WEBVTT

00:14.971 --> 00:16.451
Narrator:
AT THIS VERY MOMENT,

00:16.494 --> 00:20.107
YOUNG OLIVE SNOOK
WAS 9 YEARS, 39 WEEKS,

00:20.150 --> 00:24.807
19 HOURS, 59 MINUTES OLD,
AND DRESSED TO THE NINES.

00:24.850 --> 00:27.114
THOUGH SHE LOOKED
THE PICTURE OF PERFECTION,

00:27.157 --> 00:30.987
YOUNG OLIVE FELT THE VERY
PICTURE OF NEGLECTION.

00:31.031 --> 00:32.728
THE PARTY IN FULL SWING

00:32.771 --> 00:36.384
WAS THE CAUSE OF HER PARENTS'
CURRENT DISTRACTION.

00:36.427 --> 00:38.473
BUT YOUNG OLIVE
LEARNED A LESSON LONG AGO.

00:38.516 --> 00:41.258
SHE LEARNED HER MOTHER
AND FATHER DID NOT NEED

00:41.302 --> 00:44.740
A DIVERSION TO BE DISTRACTED
FROM THEIR DAUGHTER.

00:44.783 --> 00:48.265
YOUNG OLIVE DREAMED OF A LIFE
WHERE SHE WAS ACTIVELY LOVED

00:48.309 --> 00:50.876
AND ONLY OCCASIONALLY IGNORED.

00:50.920 --> 00:53.183
AS HAPPENS OFTEN
WITH OLIVE SNOOK,

00:53.227 --> 00:55.533
HER DREAMS CAME TRUE --

00:55.577 --> 00:58.797
JUST NOT QUITE HOW
SHE INTENDED.

00:58.841 --> 01:00.799
ACCORDING TO
HER PARENTS' TESTIMONY,

01:00.843 --> 01:02.192
YOUNG OLIVE SNOOK HAD BEEN

01:02.236 --> 01:04.194
STOLEN AWAY IN
A STOLEN VEHICLE

01:04.238 --> 01:06.718
BY DANGEROUS CAR THIEVES
AND KIDNAPPERS

01:06.762 --> 01:10.157
JERRY HOLMES
AND ROY "BUSTER" BUSTAMANTE.

01:10.200 --> 01:14.509
THEIR DAUGHTER WAS HELD FOR
1 DAY, 1 HOUR, AND 11 MINUTES

01:14.552 --> 01:17.642
BEFORE JERRY AND BUSTER
MADE THEIR FIRST RANSOM CALL.

01:17.686 --> 01:19.340
DISTRAUGHT AND HEARTBROKEN,

01:19.383 --> 01:22.734
OLIVE'S PARENTS AGREED
TO PAY THE UNDISCLOSED SUM

01:22.778 --> 01:25.694
AND CONTACTED THE POLICE.

01:25.737 --> 01:29.654
THE POLICE THEN SET A TRAP.

01:29.698 --> 01:34.833
THE LITTLE GIRL/
FUTURE JOCKEY/
PIE-WAITRESS-TO-BE

01:34.877 --> 01:38.228
WATCHED AS HER ABDUCTORS
WALKED INTO THE TRAP.

01:38.272 --> 01:40.361
JERRY HOLMES
AND BUSTER BUSTAMANTE

01:40.404 --> 01:44.234
WERE SENTENCED
TO 25 YEARS TO LIFE.

01:44.278 --> 01:49.109
8,264 HASH MARKS ON A WALL
LATER...

01:50.588 --> 01:52.024
OHH! OHH!

01:52.068 --> 01:53.591
[ GRUNTING ]

01:53.635 --> 01:55.985
Narrator: ...JERRY HOLMES
AND BUSTER BUSTAMANTE

01:56.028 --> 01:57.595
BUSTED OUT OF THE BIG HOUSE,

01:57.639 --> 02:00.468
WITH ONLY ONE PERSON
ON THEIR MIND --

02:00.511 --> 02:02.470
OLIVE SNOOK...

02:02.513 --> 02:04.689
WHO WAS, AT THIS VERY MOMENT,

02:04.733 --> 02:06.822
HANGING FROM THE PIE MAKER
SHE LOVED,

02:06.865 --> 02:09.607
WHO COULD NEVER LOVE HER,
OR SO SHE THOUGHT.

02:09.651 --> 02:12.262
I'M SORRY
YOU NEVER LOOKED AT ME

02:12.306 --> 02:13.437
THE SAME WAY
YOU LOOK AT CHUCK.

02:13.481 --> 02:15.004
I WOULDN'T SAY "NEVER."

02:15.047 --> 02:17.485
Narrator: CONFUSED --
NOT BY THE PARTICULARS,

02:17.528 --> 02:19.704
BUT BY THIS
PARTICULAR USAGE --

02:19.748 --> 02:22.533
OLIVE READ
ABOUT SENTENCE STRUCTURE

02:22.577 --> 02:24.144
AND THE USE
OF THE DOUBLE NEGATIVE

02:24.187 --> 02:27.059
AND, WITH
PASSIVE-AGGRESSIVE PANACHE,

02:27.103 --> 02:29.627
BROACHED THE SUBJECT
WITH THE PIE MAKER.

02:29.671 --> 02:31.020
TRY THIS ONE AGAIN.

02:34.763 --> 02:36.939
I DEFINITELY
DON'T HATE IT.

02:36.982 --> 02:38.375
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?
JUST WHAT I SAID.

02:38.419 --> 02:40.334
MEANS YOU LIKE IT?
YOU TELL ME.

02:40.377 --> 02:42.640
YOU SAID IT WASN'T LESS TASTY
THAN THE KICK-IN-THE-KUMQUAT,

02:42.684 --> 02:44.947
BUT MORE UNFULFILLING
THAN THE ROCK-ME-AMADE-QUINCE.

02:44.990 --> 02:47.384
I DON'T LIKE GIVING FUNNY
NAMES TO THE PIES.

02:47.428 --> 02:48.733
DOES IT NOT SEEM
DISRESPECTFUL?

02:48.777 --> 02:49.821
THERE YOU GO.
YOU DID IT AGAIN.

02:49.865 --> 02:51.997
WHAT DID I DO AGAIN?

02:52.041 --> 02:54.565
ARE YOU OKAY? YOU'VE BEEN
ACTING UNUSUAL ALL DAY.

02:54.609 --> 02:56.437
I THINK I'VE GOT
THE POST-TRAUMATIC STRESS

02:56.480 --> 02:58.613
FROM THE CLIFF DIVE
THAT ALMOST TURNED US
INTO CANYON PATTIES.

02:58.656 --> 03:00.441
WE'RE SAFE NOW, OLIVE.

03:00.484 --> 03:01.616
I KNOW, BUT THE WHOLE
THING KEEPS REPEATING

03:01.659 --> 03:03.313
ON ME OVER AND OVER,

03:03.357 --> 03:07.970
LIKE A BROKEN RECORD
OR...MEXICAN FOOD.

03:08.013 --> 03:10.625
YOU KNOW, THEY SAY
THE MORE YOU FACE YOUR TRAUMA,

03:10.668 --> 03:12.714
THE LESS POWER
IT HAS OVER YOU.

03:12.757 --> 03:16.283
OKAY. SO, THERE WE WERE,
ABOUT TO DIE...

03:16.326 --> 03:18.633
GET DOWN FROM THERE, OLIVE.
YOU'RE GONNA HURT YOURSELF.

03:18.676 --> 03:20.243
THAT'S RIGHT, NED.

03:20.287 --> 03:22.637
OH, NO, I'M SLIPPING!
I CAN'T HOLD ON MUCH LONGER!

03:22.680 --> 03:25.205
IF THERE'S ANYTHING
YOU'D LIKE TO SAY TO ME,
NOW WOULD BE THE TIME.

03:25.248 --> 03:27.381
AND IF YOU COULD SPEAK
IN THE DECLARATIVE ONLY,

03:27.424 --> 03:28.860
USING AFFIRMATIVE
OR COMPARATIVE MODIFIERS...

03:28.904 --> 03:31.211
People are eating pie!

03:31.254 --> 03:32.560
[ DOOR OPENS, BELLS RING ]

03:32.603 --> 03:33.561
DING-DONG, DADDY.

03:35.563 --> 03:36.694
DING-DONG!

03:36.738 --> 03:38.000
THAT IS HEAVEN.

03:38.043 --> 03:40.002
PEAR-WAY TO HEAVEN.
IT'S NEW.

03:40.045 --> 03:42.352
YOU KNOW, NOW THAT
I'M OUT OF DEAD-WAKING

03:42.396 --> 03:45.529
AND BACK TO JUST
PIE-BAKING AND NO LONGER
TOUCHING DEAD FRUIT,

03:45.573 --> 03:46.965
I CAN EAT MY OWN PIE.

03:47.009 --> 03:48.576
I'M GONNA GET FAT,
AREN'T I?

03:48.619 --> 03:50.795
WHILE YOU'RE BUSY GETTING FAT,
THERE'S A DEAD LADY

03:50.839 --> 03:52.710
GETTING FISHED OUT OF
THE PAPEN COUNTY FOUNTAIN,

03:52.754 --> 03:54.364
AND I GOT A GOOD FEELING
ABOUT IT.

03:54.408 --> 03:57.193
AMBULANCE SIREN'S BLARIN',
AND I GOT MY CHASIN' SHOES ON.

03:57.237 --> 03:59.978
ARE YOU SURE YOU
DON'T WANT TO UNTIE
THOSE APRON STRINGS

04:00.022 --> 04:01.589
AND LACE UP
THOSE CHASIN' LACES?

04:01.632 --> 04:05.332
MY APRON IS STAYING ON,
WITH ITS STRINGS SECURELY TIED

04:05.375 --> 04:07.203
IN A DOUBLE-FIGURE-EIGHT
FOLLOW-THROUGH KNOT.

04:07.247 --> 04:09.249
WELL, I, FOR ONE --
AND YOU SHOULD BE, FOR TWO --

04:09.292 --> 04:10.859
AM VERY SUPPORTIVE
OF YOUR DECISION.

04:10.902 --> 04:12.382
'CAUSE THAT'S
WHAT FRIENDS DO --

04:12.426 --> 04:13.862
THEY SUPPORT EACH OTHER.

04:13.905 --> 04:15.820
LOOKY HERE.

04:15.864 --> 04:18.954
YES, THE ZAPPITY-ZAP
NEARLY TURNED EVERYTHING
TO CRAPPITY-CRAP

04:18.997 --> 04:21.217
ON ACCOUNT OF DEAD GIRL AND
HER DIGGING-UP-DEAD-DADDY.

04:21.261 --> 04:23.263
I APOLOGIZED FOR THAT.

04:23.306 --> 04:26.135
I WANT TO LEAD A NORMAL LIFE
OF A GUY WHO JUST MAKES PIES.

04:26.178 --> 04:28.746
WHO WANTS TO BE SUPERMAN?
NOT ME.

04:28.790 --> 04:32.054
I SAY NO TO "SUPER"
AND YES TO "MAN."

04:32.097 --> 04:33.882
I'M CLARK KENT.

04:33.925 --> 04:36.972
WELL, THAT'S JUST
DOWNRIGHT CRAP-TASTIC, CLARK.

04:37.015 --> 04:39.322
I NOW HAVE AN ABNORMALLY LARGE
AMOUNT OF WORK TO DO

04:39.366 --> 04:42.282
ON ACCOUNT OF NO ONE HERE
WANTS TO TOUCH A DEAD LADY

04:42.325 --> 04:43.500
SO I CAN ASK
WHO KILLED HER.

04:43.544 --> 04:45.285
HMM.

04:45.328 --> 04:46.547
Chuck:
EMERSON! EMERSON!

04:46.590 --> 04:48.026
WHAT ABOUT ME?

04:48.070 --> 04:49.637
NO CONVERSATION I
EVER WANT TO HAVE

04:49.680 --> 04:50.725
BEGINS WITH THOSE
THREE WORDS

04:50.768 --> 04:52.248
I GOT WORK TO DO.

04:52.292 --> 04:53.684
YEAH, BUT WORK THAT YOU DON'T
HAVE TO DO ALONE.

04:53.728 --> 04:55.338
I MEAN,
I MAY NOT BE SUPERMAN,

04:55.382 --> 04:57.122
BUT I'M SMART
AND I'M HELPFUL.

04:57.166 --> 05:00.169
I MEAN...MAYBE I COULD BE
YOUR SIDEKICK.

05:00.212 --> 05:01.997
I COULD BE
THE ALIVE-AGAIN AVENGER

05:02.040 --> 05:03.390
WHO CAME BACK FROM THE DEAD
TO SOLVE HER OWN MURDER

05:03.433 --> 05:04.913
AND STAYED BACK
FROM THE DEAD

05:04.956 --> 05:06.915
TO BRING JUSTICE
TO MURDER VICTIMS EVERYWHERE,

05:06.958 --> 05:08.438
WITH THE HELP OF
A CRUSTY, UNFLAPPABLE,

05:08.482 --> 05:09.744
STREETWISE GUMSHOE.

05:09.787 --> 05:11.398
THAT'D MAKE ME
THE SIDEKICK.

05:11.441 --> 05:13.487
I'M GOOD EITHER WAY.

05:13.530 --> 05:15.619
ALRIGHT, THEN,
SIDEKICK AVENGER,

05:15.663 --> 05:19.101
SINCE WE NO LONGER HAVE
SUPERMAN AND HIS SUPER FINGER,

05:19.144 --> 05:22.365
YOU MUST KNOW THIS IS AN
ENTIRELY DIFFERENT BALLGAME.

05:22.409 --> 05:24.454
THIS GAME IS
ALL ABOUT THE HUSTLE.

05:24.498 --> 05:25.499
OH, I LOVE THE HUSTLE.

05:28.502 --> 05:30.025
[ SIREN WAILS ]

05:35.726 --> 05:37.728
BODY'S BEEN IDENTIFIED
OFF AN EMPLOYEE I.D.

05:37.772 --> 05:39.643
FROM DICKER'S
DEPARTMENT STORE

05:39.687 --> 05:40.775
AS ERIN EMBRY.

05:40.818 --> 05:43.125
Chuck:
WHAT IS THAT SMELL?

05:43.168 --> 05:44.735
IT SMELLS LIKE AUNT LILY
ON A SUNDAY --

05:44.779 --> 05:46.128
I MEAN,
MY MOM ON A SUNDAY.

05:46.171 --> 05:47.695
SINGLE-MALT SCOTCH --

05:47.738 --> 05:49.523
SOMETHING I COULD USE
A SHOT OF RIGHT NOW.

05:49.566 --> 05:51.742
COPS THINK
THIS WAS AN ACCIDENT.

05:51.786 --> 05:53.309
WOMAN STILL IN
THE HOLIDAY SPIRIT

05:53.353 --> 05:54.745
GUZZLES TOO MANY SPIRITS,

05:54.789 --> 05:56.791
DOES A GENE-KELLY-
'ROUND-THE-ROSY,

05:56.834 --> 05:59.271
SLIPS, BONKS HER NOGGIN,
ENDS UP IN THE FOUNTAIN.

05:59.315 --> 06:02.100
WHICH FROZE WHEN THE
TEMPERATURES DIPPED OVERNIGHT.

06:02.144 --> 06:03.493
THIS IS JUST A GREAT
BIG WASTE OF MY TIME.

06:03.537 --> 06:04.842
AIN'T NO CASE HERE.

06:04.886 --> 06:06.496
I-I'M NOT DONE
WITH THE HUSTLE.

06:06.540 --> 06:08.455
WELL, YOU'RE GONNA BE
DANCIN' BY YOURSELF.

06:10.674 --> 06:13.155
Narrator: BUT INSTEAD
OF DANCING BY HERSELF,

06:13.198 --> 06:15.810
CHUCK FOUND ANOTHER PARTNER
TO HOLD HER HAND,

06:15.853 --> 06:17.507
IN THE ONLY WAY HE COULD.

06:17.551 --> 06:19.553
WINTER IS
MY NEW BEST FRIEND.

06:19.596 --> 06:20.815
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:20.858 --> 06:22.382
WE SHOULD MOVE
TO THE SOUTH POLE.

06:22.425 --> 06:23.557
ALTHOUGH I DON'T KNOW
IF THEY HAVE A NEED FOR PIE

06:23.600 --> 06:25.123
IN THE SOUTH POLE,

06:25.167 --> 06:27.691
WHICH PUTS A WRINKLE
IN MY FRESHLY STARCHED LIFE

06:27.735 --> 06:29.519
AS A NORMAL GUY
WHO MAKES PIES.

06:29.563 --> 06:32.000
BUT I'D GIVE IT UP IF I COULD
HOLD YOUR HAND EVERY DAY.

06:32.043 --> 06:34.350
WHAT, THE PIE OR THE NORMAL?
EITHER.

06:34.394 --> 06:37.527
BUT I'D PREFER TO HAVE MY PIE
AND "NORMAL" IT, TOO.

06:37.571 --> 06:38.702
WHERE WE GOING?

06:38.746 --> 06:40.356
DICKER'S
DEPARTMENT STORE.

06:40.400 --> 06:42.271
THAT POOR GIRL, ERIN EMBRY,
WAS MURDERED,

06:42.314 --> 06:44.012
AND SHE USED TO WORK
IN DICKER'S.

06:44.055 --> 06:45.970
M-MURDERED? I THOUGHT
HER DEATH WAS AN ACCIDENT.

06:46.014 --> 06:47.537
NO, THEY DISMISSED IT
AS AN ACCIDENT,

06:47.581 --> 06:49.365
BUT THEY DISMISS MURDERS
AS ACCIDENTS EVERY DAY.

06:49.409 --> 06:51.411
THEY COULD HAVE DISMISSED
MY MURDER AS AN ACCIDENT.

06:51.454 --> 06:53.500
THEY COULD HAVE SAID THAT
I SLIPPED AND FELL OVERBOARD,

06:53.543 --> 06:55.197
AS OPPOSED TO
WHAT REALLY HAPPENED --

06:55.240 --> 06:58.156
I WAS STRANGLED
AND THROWN OVERBOARD.

06:58.200 --> 06:59.984
IS THIS DICKER'S
DEPARTMENT STORE?

07:00.028 --> 07:01.769
UH-HUH.
[ GASPS ]

07:01.812 --> 07:04.424
THAT IS JUST LIKE THE FOUNTAIN
WHERE ERIN DIED!

07:04.467 --> 07:06.121
THAT COCKTAIL-SWILLING
MANNEQUIN

07:06.164 --> 07:08.253
IS WEARING THE EXACT SAME
DRESS ERIN WAS WEARING.

07:08.297 --> 07:09.690
AND THE SAME SHOES.

07:09.733 --> 07:11.779
THIS IS THE SCENE
OF THE CRIME!

07:11.822 --> 07:13.563
YAY!
THE ALIVE-AGAIN AVENGER!

07:13.607 --> 07:14.825
YAY! YAY!

07:14.869 --> 07:16.348
COME ON,
LET'S GO FIND EMERSON

07:16.392 --> 07:17.524
AND TELL HIM THAT ERIN EMBRY'S
MURDER IS DISPLAYED

07:17.567 --> 07:19.134
IN DICKER'S
DEPARTMENT STORE.

07:19.177 --> 07:22.354
I-I'M NOT AN AVENGER.
I'M A PIE MAKER.

07:22.398 --> 07:25.488
I'M NOT GONNA PRETEND
TO BE SOMETHING I'M NOT.
IT'S STRESSFUL.

07:25.532 --> 07:28.099
SO I'M GONNA GO TO
THE PIE HOLE AND MAKE
MY MONIKER PROUD.

07:28.143 --> 07:30.885
WELL, I'M GONNA GO AND AVENGE
AND MAKE MY MONIKER PROUD.

07:30.928 --> 07:34.105
WHO NEEDS SUPERMAN?
YOU'RE MY HERO.

07:34.149 --> 07:35.150
AW. [ SMOOCHES ]

07:37.282 --> 07:40.155
Narrator:
WHILE THE PIE MAKER LINGERED
ON HIS ALIVE-AGAIN AVENGER...

07:40.198 --> 07:44.376
RANDY MANN, A TAXIDERMIST
WHO ONCE PAID FOR FRIENDS,

07:44.420 --> 07:47.075
CAME TO THE PIE HOLE
BEARING A GIFT.

07:47.118 --> 07:50.382
BUT SAID GIFT WASN'T THE FIRST
PRIORITY OF HIS VISIT.

07:50.426 --> 07:51.558
HEIGH-HO, PIE-BRO!

07:51.601 --> 07:52.950
WHO YOU CALLING "HO"?

07:52.994 --> 07:54.386
OH.

07:54.430 --> 07:55.431
RANDY MANN.

07:57.694 --> 08:00.436
MISS OLIVE, UH, I MEANT
NO OFFENSE BY THAT "HO."

08:00.480 --> 08:04.135
THE INTENT WAS TO BE JOLLY,
NOT DEROGATORY.

08:04.179 --> 08:05.615
IS THE PIE MAKER PRESENT?

08:05.659 --> 08:07.835
UNH-UNH.
NO?

08:07.878 --> 08:09.140
I'LL WAIT.

08:09.184 --> 08:10.707
CAN I GET YOU
A SLICE OF PIE?

08:10.751 --> 08:12.753
ONE SLICE
OF EVERYTHING, PLEASE.

08:12.796 --> 08:14.798
[ CHUCKLES ] STARTING
WITH YOUR FAVORITE OF THE DAY.

08:14.842 --> 08:16.670
I DON'T THINK EATING THAT
MUCH FRUIT IS WISE.

08:16.713 --> 08:18.019
OH.

08:18.062 --> 08:19.716
ARE THOSE THE BIRDS
NED HAD YOU STUFF?

08:19.760 --> 08:21.936
YEAH, A BIRTHDAY PRESENT
FOR HIS MAGICIAN BROTHERS.

08:21.979 --> 08:23.024
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:23.067 --> 08:24.460
Wow.

08:24.504 --> 08:26.984
"WOW'S" GOOD, RIGHT?
"WOW" MEANS YOU LIKE IT?

08:27.028 --> 08:28.464
MM...YEAH.

08:28.508 --> 08:31.336
BOY, YOU SURE DO
TURN THOSE BIRDS AROUND FAST.

08:31.380 --> 08:33.425
WHEN STARTING
A NEW BUSINESS VENTURE,

08:33.469 --> 08:36.037
IT'S IMPORTANT NOT TO KEEP
THE CUSTOMER WAITIN'.

08:36.080 --> 08:37.821
Narrator:
MORE IMPORTANT TO RANDY MANN

08:37.865 --> 08:41.172
WAS KEEPING HIMSELF FROM
WAITING TO SEE OLIVE SNOOK.

08:41.216 --> 08:43.784
[ DOOR OPENS, BELLS RING ]
AND HE WASN'T THE ONLY PERSON

08:43.827 --> 08:46.047
WHO COULDN'T WAIT
TO SEE OLIVE SNOOK.

08:46.090 --> 08:47.570
Jiminy convicts!

08:47.614 --> 08:48.789
Those are the guys
that kidnapped me

08:48.832 --> 08:49.833
when I was a little girl.

08:52.270 --> 08:53.489
SNOOK.
SNOOK.

08:57.972 --> 09:00.104
Narrator:
OLIVE SNOOK HAD CLOSED EARLY,

09:00.148 --> 09:04.587
BUT NOT DUE TO A LACKADAISICAL
WORK ETHIC OR LACK OF PATRONS.

09:04.631 --> 09:05.806
Ned:
OH, MY GOD. RANDY.

09:05.849 --> 09:07.329
OLIVE,
DID YOU HIT HIM?

09:07.372 --> 09:09.418
DID SHE HIT YOU?
NO, HE HIT ME.

09:09.461 --> 09:12.290
I GOT A LOW PLATELET COUNT
AND 0% BODY FAT.

09:12.334 --> 09:15.816
THAT'S A ONE-TWO PUNCH
FOR BRUISING.

09:15.859 --> 09:18.558
THAT'D BE FUNNY IF I HADN'T
BEEN THE ONE WHO GOT PUNCHED.

09:18.601 --> 09:20.385
I TOLD YOU NOT TO DO IT.
I TOLD HIM NOT TO DO IT.

09:20.429 --> 09:22.344
SUCKER PUNCH.
YOU'RE A SUCKER-PUNCHER!

09:22.387 --> 09:24.955
TAKE IT EASY,
TOUGH GUY.

09:24.999 --> 09:26.087
COULD HAVE BEEN
A WHOLE LOT WORSE.

09:26.130 --> 09:27.610
OLIVE, WHO ARE THESE GUYS?

09:27.654 --> 09:31.222
WHO ARE ANY OF US,
REALLY?

09:31.266 --> 09:32.876
THEY'RE HER
CHILDHOOD KIDNAPPERS.

09:32.920 --> 09:36.619
UH, THEY WEREN'T
EXACTLY KIDNAPPERS.

09:36.663 --> 09:39.970
Narrator: WHAT THEY WERE,
EXACTLY, WAS THIS --

09:40.014 --> 09:42.146
JERRY AND BUSTER
WERE PETTY THIEVES,

09:42.190 --> 09:43.844
BUT THEY WERE NOT KIDNAPPERS.

09:43.887 --> 09:46.847
THEY WERE IN THE WRONG CAR
AT THE WRONG TIME

09:46.890 --> 09:48.588
AND WERE NOT ALONE.

09:48.631 --> 09:50.328
YOUNG OLIVE SNOOK
HAD STOWED AWAY

09:50.372 --> 09:52.200
IN THEIR RECENTLY STOLEN CAR,

09:52.243 --> 09:55.899
HOPING THE OLD ADAGE "ABSENCE
MAKES THE HEART GROW FONDER"

09:55.943 --> 09:58.336
WOULD TEACH HER NEGLECTFUL
PARENTS A LESSON.

09:58.380 --> 10:01.296
JERRY AND BUSTER WANTED
TO RETURN THE LITTLE GIRL

10:01.339 --> 10:02.471
TO HER PARENTS RIGHT AWAY...

10:02.514 --> 10:04.081
WHAT'S YOUR NAME,
PICKLE?

10:04.125 --> 10:06.040
Narrator:
...BUT, DESPITE THEIR
ATTEMPTS,

10:06.083 --> 10:08.869
SHE REFUSED
TO TELL THEM HER NAME.

10:08.912 --> 10:12.481
THEIR ARGUMENT WAS HUSHED
SO YOUNG OLIVE WOULD NOT HEAR

10:12.524 --> 10:16.659
THAT REPEATED CALLS TO HER
PARENTS HAD GONE UNANSWERED

10:16.703 --> 10:19.880
AND SO AS NOT TO DISTURB
OLIVE'S LOVE OF CARTOONS.

10:21.925 --> 10:24.232
[ LAUGHTER ]

10:24.275 --> 10:26.147
Narrator:
THE 2 DAYS, 12 HOURS,

10:26.190 --> 10:28.540
AND 19 MINUTES
YOUNG OLIVE SNOOK SPENT

10:28.584 --> 10:31.413
WITH JERRY HOLMES
AND BUSTER BUSTAMANTE

10:31.456 --> 10:35.460
WERE THE BEST 2 DAYS,
12 HOURS, AND 19 MINUTES

10:35.504 --> 10:37.462
OF HER YOUNG LIFE.

10:37.506 --> 10:41.379
IT WAS ALSO THE BEST
OF THEIRS.

10:41.423 --> 10:44.774
AFTER EXPLAINING THE
SITUATION, THEY REALIZED

10:44.818 --> 10:48.212
YOUNG OLIVE'S PARENTS HADN'T
EVEN KNOWN SHE WAS GONE.

10:48.256 --> 10:50.084
THEY CONFRONTED THE SNOOKS

10:50.127 --> 10:52.608
ON THEIR DERELICT
PARENTING SKILLS.

10:52.652 --> 10:56.481
MOM AND DAD SNOOK TOOK UMBRAGE
AND CALLED THE AUTHORITIES.

10:56.525 --> 10:59.963
AS IT WAS THEIR WORD AGAINST
THE WORD OF TWO PETTY THIEVES,

11:00.007 --> 11:02.487
THE NOW-ACCUSED
KIDNAPPERS WERE SENT AWAY

11:02.531 --> 11:04.751
FOR THE MAXIMUM
THE LAW WOULD ALLOW.

11:04.794 --> 11:08.058
KNOWING WHAT SHE'D LOST
THE MINUTE THEY WERE GONE,

11:08.102 --> 11:11.322
YOUNG OLIVE VOWED
TO KEEP IN TOUCH.

11:11.366 --> 11:14.412
SHE WROTE THEM EVERY WEEK
AND NEVER FORGOT.

11:14.456 --> 11:17.807
AND THEY, IN TURN,
NEVER FORGOT HER.

11:17.851 --> 11:19.940
DID YOU GUYS
JUST GET OUT?

11:19.983 --> 11:21.985
UH...JUST.
ESCAPED.

11:22.029 --> 11:23.334
THE WORD THAT'S SUPPOSED
TO FOLLOW THAT "JUST"

11:23.378 --> 11:24.727
IS "ESCAPED."

11:24.771 --> 11:26.773
Jerry: HOLDING A GRUDGE
OVER THE SHINER.

11:26.816 --> 11:28.296
A GRUDGE-HOLDER, HUH?

11:28.339 --> 11:30.124
IT'S SO WONDERFUL
THAT YOU CAME TO SEE ME.

11:30.167 --> 11:32.256
Ned: IT WON'T BE WONDERFUL
WHEN THE POLICE SHOW UP

11:32.300 --> 11:34.345
LOOKING FOR EX-CONS AND HAPPEN
UPON SOME OTHER EX-PEOPLE

11:34.389 --> 11:35.651
WE'D RATHER
THEY DIDN'T HAPPEN UPON.

11:35.695 --> 11:38.523
WHICH IS WHY
WE NEED OUR SNOOK HERE

11:38.567 --> 11:40.047
TO HELP GET US
ACROSS THE BORDER.

11:40.090 --> 11:41.701
IT'S THE LEAST I CAN DO.

11:41.744 --> 11:43.354
YOU NEVER SHOULD
HAVE GONE TO JAIL,

11:43.398 --> 11:45.530
BUT NO ONE WOULD BELIEVE ME
THAT I RAN AWAY.

11:45.574 --> 11:47.271
WHAT DO WE ALWAYS SAY
ABOUT THE PAST?

11:47.315 --> 11:49.186
IT MAKES AN ASS
OUT OF YOU AND ME.

11:49.230 --> 11:50.971
Ned: CAN WE GO BACK
TO "ESCAPED FROM JAIL"?

11:51.014 --> 11:52.973
OR AM I THE ONLY ONE
WHO FINDS THAT TROUBLING?

11:53.016 --> 11:54.496
WHO'S THE WORRY WART?

11:54.539 --> 11:56.063
THAT'S NED.
HE OWNS THE PLACE.

11:56.106 --> 11:57.281
THE PIE MAKER? THE PIE MAKER?

11:57.325 --> 11:58.892
UH, BOYS?

11:58.935 --> 12:01.851
NUDGE YOUR GRUDGE OFF OF
THAT STOOL, CRANKY-PANTS,

12:01.895 --> 12:03.810
SO I CAN GET A GOOD LOOK
AT THE BAKER MAN

12:03.853 --> 12:06.029
WHO'S GONNA MARRY
OUR LITTLE GIRL.

12:06.073 --> 12:07.901
AAH...

12:07.944 --> 12:09.032
BUT I THOUGHT YOU WERE --

12:09.076 --> 12:11.687
ACTUALLY...UH...

12:11.731 --> 12:12.862
OLIVE?

12:12.906 --> 12:13.907
OLIVE.

12:13.950 --> 12:14.995
HUH?

12:15.038 --> 12:17.867
UM...ME AND OLIVE...

12:17.911 --> 12:20.174
Narrator:
THE PIE MAKER CONSIDERED
HOW THE TRUTH

12:20.217 --> 12:21.566
WOULD HUMILIATE OLIVE

12:21.610 --> 12:23.873
AND DEVASTATE THE
TWO SWEET MEN

12:23.917 --> 12:25.396
WHOSE ONLY HAPPINESS CAME

12:25.440 --> 12:27.790
FROM KNOWING THE LITTLE GIRL
THEY LOVED MOST

12:27.834 --> 12:30.619
WAS LOVED MOST BY
THE PIE MAKER.

12:30.662 --> 12:31.663
SO HE SAID...

12:31.707 --> 12:34.928
ME AND OLIVE...

12:34.971 --> 12:36.277
...LOVE EACH OTHER
VERY MUCH.

12:38.714 --> 12:43.893
Narrator: AND, ONCE AGAIN,
OLIVE'S DREAM CAME TRUE --

12:43.937 --> 12:45.547
JUST NOT QUITE
HOW SHE INTENDED.

12:48.637 --> 12:50.595
OLIVE TOLD ME
ALL ABOUT JERRY AND BUSTER

12:50.639 --> 12:51.814
DURING ONE OF OUR
LATE-NIGHT GIRL TALKS,

12:51.858 --> 12:53.424
AND WE USUALLY TALK
ABOUT OLIVE,

12:53.468 --> 12:55.426
'CAUSE, SEE, I'M A KIND OF
ALL-OR-NOTHING KIND OF GIRL,

12:55.470 --> 12:57.385
SO SEEING AS I CAN'T
TELL HER THE TRUTH --

12:57.428 --> 12:59.909
[ SNORING ]

12:59.953 --> 13:01.476
LITTLE PEEWEE
BOTHER TO MENTION

13:01.519 --> 13:03.565
THAT SHE TOLD PAPA NUMBER ONE
AND PAPA NUMBER TWO

13:03.608 --> 13:05.697
THAT YOUR MAN
AIN'T YOUR MAN -- HE'S HERS?

13:05.741 --> 13:07.569
NO, SHE DIDN'T.

13:07.612 --> 13:08.875
LOANING PIE-BOYFRIEND
TO YOUR BESTIE,

13:08.918 --> 13:10.528
WHO'S IN LOVE WITH HIM,

13:10.572 --> 13:12.443
IN ORDER TO PULL THE WOOL
OVER FAKE PAPAS' PEEPERS

13:12.487 --> 13:14.837
IS THE KIND OF IDEA
THAT GIVES A BAD IDEA
THE WILL TO LIVE.

13:14.881 --> 13:17.318
YEAH, AND THAT'S WHY I'M
PEEVED. I CAN'T AVENGE
WHEN I'M PEEVED.

13:17.361 --> 13:18.493
YOU ARE NO GOOD TO ME
FOCUSING ON YOUR LADY PEEVES.

13:18.536 --> 13:20.147
YOU NEED TO FOCUS ON --

13:20.190 --> 13:23.280
AND NOW NED AND OLIVE ARE ON
A ROMANTIC RUN TO THE BORDER.

13:23.324 --> 13:25.282
ACTUALLY, I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHY I'M UPSET.

13:25.326 --> 13:27.676
IT'S JUST FOR ONE DAY.
I'M BEING RIDICULOUS.

13:27.719 --> 13:29.373
A LOT CAN HAPPEN
IN A DAY.

13:29.417 --> 13:31.985
SO, IS THIS THE FINAL REPOSE
OF ERIN EMBRY?

13:32.028 --> 13:33.116
THAT'S MY THEORY.

13:33.160 --> 13:34.857
NICE HUSTLE,
SIDEKICK AVENGER.

13:34.901 --> 13:37.207
LOOKS TO ME ERIN EMBRY
WAS MORE THAN

13:37.251 --> 13:39.601
JUST SOME SPRITZER GIRL ANNOYING
FOLKS WITH HER PERFUME.

13:39.644 --> 13:41.472
ERIN WASN'T ANNOYING PEOPLE.

13:41.516 --> 13:44.214
SHE WAS DAZZLING THEM
WITH FANTASTIC WORLDS CREATED

13:44.258 --> 13:46.477
WITHIN THE PROSCENIUM ARCH
OF THE DICKER'S WINDOW FRAME.

13:46.521 --> 13:48.001
ERIN EMBRY
DRESSED THIS WINDOW?

13:48.044 --> 13:49.480
ALONG WITH HER PARTNER,
COCO JUNIPER.

13:49.524 --> 13:52.005
ALTHOUGH IT WAS
COMMON KNOWLEDGE

13:52.048 --> 13:53.658
THAT ERIN WAS THE ONE
WITH THE TRUE TALENT.

13:53.702 --> 13:55.878
ERIN COULD DO THINGS
WITH A MANNEQUIN

13:55.922 --> 13:57.532
COCO COULD NEVER DO.

13:57.575 --> 13:59.229
WHO IN THE HELL
ARE YOU PEOPLE?

13:59.273 --> 14:01.666
WE'RE DEVOTEES --
FANS OF ERIN

14:01.710 --> 14:03.190
AND, TO A LESSER
EXTENT, COCO'S.

14:03.233 --> 14:06.410
BUT WE PREFER
THE TERM "DEVOTEES."

14:08.282 --> 14:10.937
ANY OF THESE "DEVOTEES"
SEEM A LITTLE OVERLY DEVOTED?

14:10.980 --> 14:12.677
APPROPRIATELY DEVOTED,

14:12.721 --> 14:14.810
BUT OVERLY DEVASTATED
BY ERIN'S DEATH,

14:14.854 --> 14:16.725
WHICH IS SOON
TO BE AVENGED.

14:16.768 --> 14:19.336
IF THE ALIVE-AGAIN AVENGER
HUSTLES THIS CASE TO FRUITION,

14:19.380 --> 14:20.860
AM I STILL THE SIDEKICK?

14:20.903 --> 14:22.078
YES.

14:22.122 --> 14:23.601
AND IF THE ALIVE-AGAIN AVENGER

14:23.645 --> 14:25.299
REALLY WANTED TO HUSTLE,
SHE'D GET ME PAID.

14:29.738 --> 14:30.957
IS IT TRUE?
ERIN WAS MURDERED?

14:31.000 --> 14:32.088
MURDERED?!

14:32.132 --> 14:33.655
THAT'S WHAT HE SAID.

14:33.698 --> 14:35.744
ISN'T THAT PRIVATE
INVESTIGATOR EMERSON COD?

14:35.787 --> 14:38.529
NOW, WHY WOULD HE BE HERE
IF THERE WAS NO FOUL PLAY?

14:38.573 --> 14:40.314
WHY WOULD HE BE HERE
IF THERE WAS NO FOUL PLAY?

14:40.357 --> 14:42.098
YOU KNOW, I WOULD GIVE
MY LAST NICKEL TO THAT MAN

14:42.142 --> 14:43.621
TO FIND OUT WHAT
REALLY HAPPENED TO ERIN

14:43.665 --> 14:44.927
AND BRING THAT
KILLER TO JUSTICE!

14:44.971 --> 14:47.103
YEAH! SO WOULD I!
ME TOO!

14:47.147 --> 14:48.365
ME TOO!

14:48.409 --> 14:51.107
Together: WE ALL WOULD!

14:51.151 --> 14:52.674
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

14:52.717 --> 14:55.285
♪ DICKER'S DEPARTMENT STORE

14:55.329 --> 14:56.678
WELCOME TO DICKER'S.

14:56.721 --> 14:58.245
I'M DICK DICKER,
OWNER AND PROPRIETOR.

14:58.288 --> 15:00.812
WHAT CAN I HELP YOU FINE
FOLKS FIND TODAY?

15:00.856 --> 15:02.640
A NEW FRILLY FROCK
FOR THE MISSUS?

15:02.684 --> 15:05.861
A BESPOKE PINSTRIPE FROM
THE B&T SECTION FOR YOU, SIR?

15:05.905 --> 15:07.515
POCKET SQUARE, MAY-HAPS?

15:07.558 --> 15:09.386
MY NAME'S EMERSON COD.
I'M A PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR.

15:09.430 --> 15:11.519
MY...ASSOCIATE
AND I WERE HIRED

15:11.562 --> 15:15.131
TO LOOK INTO
ERIN EMBRY'S DEATH.

15:15.175 --> 15:17.003
I'M CONFUSED.

15:17.046 --> 15:18.613
WHY WOULD YOU BE HIRED
TO LOOK INTO SOMETHING

15:18.656 --> 15:21.007
THAT THE POLICE ALREADY
DECIDED WAS AN ACCIDENT?

15:21.050 --> 15:22.617
A TRAGIC ONE AT THAT.

15:22.660 --> 15:24.140
WELL, IT STILL VERY WELL
MAY BE, MR. DICKER,

15:24.184 --> 15:26.273
BUT THAT'S WHAT WE INTEND
TO FIND OUT.

15:26.316 --> 15:29.015
WAS, UH, ERIN DOING WELL
HERE AT DICKER'S?

15:29.058 --> 15:30.581
ERIN WAS DOING VERY WELL
HERE AT DICKER'S,

15:30.625 --> 15:33.410
AND DICKER'S WAS DOING VERY
WELL BECAUSE OF ERIN.

15:33.454 --> 15:36.500
AND, TO A LESSER
EXTENT, COCO.

15:36.544 --> 15:37.937
COCO JUNIPER?

15:37.980 --> 15:39.416
OH, YES.

15:39.460 --> 15:41.679
ERIN AND COCO'S
PERFECTLY DRESSED WINDOWS

15:41.723 --> 15:44.204
CREATED CONGESTION
IN PEDESTRIAN TRAFFIC.

15:44.247 --> 15:46.728
WHICH CREATED A LOOKY-LOO
GRIDLOCK ZONE

15:46.771 --> 15:48.512
AT OUR FRONT DOOR.

15:48.556 --> 15:51.385
WHICH CREATED AN OVERFLOW
OF POTENTIAL PURCHASERS

15:51.428 --> 15:53.082
FUNNELING THROUGH THAT DOOR.

15:53.126 --> 15:55.345
WHICH CREATED RETAIL SALES.

15:55.389 --> 15:58.000
THEIR WORK HERE
MEANT EVERYTHING TO DICKER'S.

15:58.044 --> 16:00.307
ANY IDEA IF THAT COLLABORATION
WAS COPACETIC?

16:00.350 --> 16:02.744
DICKER'S IS
A FAMILY STORE.

16:02.787 --> 16:04.833
ERIN WAS
A PART OF THAT FAMILY.

16:04.876 --> 16:08.489
THIS STORE, ITS EMPLOYEES,
AND THOSE PEOPLE OUTSIDE

16:08.532 --> 16:10.447
ARE IN MOURNING --

16:10.491 --> 16:12.101
NO ONE MORE SO...

16:12.145 --> 16:14.364
THAN COCO JUNIPER.

16:14.408 --> 16:16.932
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

16:16.976 --> 16:18.281
HMM...

16:18.325 --> 16:19.456
UH...

16:19.500 --> 16:20.457
UH-HUH.

16:20.501 --> 16:21.502
WELL.

16:21.545 --> 16:23.591
IT'S SO...SO...

16:23.634 --> 16:25.941
UHH...WRONG.

16:25.985 --> 16:29.031
NO, "WRONG" WOULD BE RELATIVE,
AS IF YOU HAD IN SOME WAY

16:29.075 --> 16:30.250
GOTTEN WITHIN THE REALM

16:30.293 --> 16:31.468
OF WHAT WOULD BE
CONSIDERED RIGHT.

16:31.512 --> 16:32.513
ARE YOU WINCING?

16:32.556 --> 16:34.167
NO.

16:34.210 --> 16:35.298
Chuck: [ CLEARS THROAT ]
COCO, ABOUT ERIN?

16:35.342 --> 16:36.691
ERIN EMBRY
WAS MY PARTNER.

16:36.734 --> 16:38.519
DIDN'T KNOW
UNTIL SHE WAS GONE

16:38.562 --> 16:40.564
THAT SHE WAS ALSO
MY INSPIRATION AND MY LIGHT.

16:40.608 --> 16:43.045
BECAUSE WITHOUT ERIN EMBRY,
I'M LEFT WITH...

16:43.089 --> 16:44.699
A-AND YOURSELF.

16:44.742 --> 16:46.092
I MEAN, SO WHAT
IF ERIN COULD DO THINGS

16:46.135 --> 16:47.745
WITH A MANNEQUIN
THAT YOU COULD NEVER DO?

16:47.789 --> 16:50.313
WHO SAID ERIN COULD DO THINGS
WITH A MANNEQUIN

16:50.357 --> 16:51.706
THAT I COULD NEVER DO?

16:51.749 --> 16:53.664
I NEVER SAID THAT --
EVER.

16:53.708 --> 16:56.363
[ CHUCKLES ] WELL, DESPITE
WHAT YOU MAY HAVE HEARD,

16:56.406 --> 16:58.017
I CARRIED ERIN.

16:58.060 --> 17:00.628
I WAS JUST BEING
GRACIOUS BEFORE.

17:00.671 --> 17:02.673
YOU ARE AWARE
THAT ERIN DIED IN A SCENARIO

17:02.717 --> 17:04.284
EXACTLY LIKE THE ONE DEPICTED

17:04.327 --> 17:05.894
IN YOUR WINDOW
OF THE PAPEN FOUNTAIN?

17:05.937 --> 17:08.288
YOU REALIZE
THAT MAKES YOU A SUSPECT?

17:08.331 --> 17:10.638
YES, ALONG WITH EVERYBODY
ELSE IN THIS ROOM.

17:10.681 --> 17:12.074
DENNY, DID YOU KILL ERIN?

17:12.118 --> 17:13.162
NO, COCO.

17:13.206 --> 17:15.469
NEITHER DID I.
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:15.512 --> 17:16.687
UH...
WHAT'S -- WHAT'S THIS?

17:16.731 --> 17:18.385
OH, IT'S FOR
THE MEMORIAL WINDOW.

17:18.428 --> 17:19.908
I THINK IT'S CHIC AS HELL.
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:19.951 --> 17:21.649
OR IT'S GOING TO BE.

17:21.692 --> 17:23.564
DENNY, IF THIS IS WHAT YOU
THINK IS CHIC AS HELL,

17:23.607 --> 17:25.392
THEN COULD YOU GO BACK
TO PAIRING BOBBY-SOCKS

17:25.435 --> 17:26.871
AND TRAINING BRAS
IN THE JUNIORS DEPARTMENT?

17:26.915 --> 17:28.786
[ CHUCKLES ]
[ SIGHS ]

17:28.830 --> 17:32.225
WE'RE UNVEILING THE ERIN EMBRY
MEMORIAL WINDOW TONIGHT.

17:32.268 --> 17:34.053
IT'S MY UNVEILING, TOO.

17:34.096 --> 17:38.274
EVERYONE WILL SEE ONCE AND FOR
ALL WHO CAN DO WHAT.

17:38.318 --> 17:40.537
EXCUSE US.

17:40.581 --> 17:43.149
MAYBE COCO'S GONE LOCO
AND SHE KILLED ERIN

17:43.192 --> 17:44.846
SO SHE COULD HAVE
HER FIRST SOLO WINDOW.

17:44.889 --> 17:46.761
YEAH, WE NEED TO BE
AT THAT UNVEILING TONIGHT

17:46.804 --> 17:48.328
JUST IN CASE
COCO DID GO LOCO,

17:48.371 --> 17:50.765
FO-SHO...CO.

17:50.808 --> 17:53.202
Narrator: WHAT EMERSON AND
CHUCK DID NOT KNOW WAS,

17:53.246 --> 17:56.553
AS THEY TOOK A LONG, HARD LOOK
AT THE MAIN SUSPECT THEY HAD,

17:56.597 --> 18:01.558
THE KILLER WAS TAKING
A LONG, HARD LOOK AT THEM.

18:06.781 --> 18:09.088
Narrator: AT THIS VERY MOMENT,
RANDY MANN WAS CONFUSED.

18:09.131 --> 18:11.133
I'M CONFUSED.
I THOUGHT YOU AND CHU--

18:11.177 --> 18:12.482
NOT A GOOD TIME, RANDY.

18:12.526 --> 18:14.702
SORRY ABOUT
THE CRAMPED QUARTERS.

18:14.745 --> 18:16.704
I JUST GOT A NEW ACCOUNT
WITH THE ZOO.

18:16.747 --> 18:18.662
THERE IS A VERY
LUCRATIVE AFTERMARKET

18:18.706 --> 18:20.316
FOR EXOTIC ANIMALS.

18:20.360 --> 18:23.580
ALOISIUS BACK THERE IS GOING
TO A MAJOR RETAIL OUTLET

18:23.624 --> 18:25.713
TO PROMOTE BIG SAVINGS.

18:25.756 --> 18:27.802
HOP UP ON YOUR GUY'S LAP
THERE, OKAY?

18:27.845 --> 18:30.283
MY JINGLE'S GOTTA HAVE
SOME ROOM TO JANGLE.

18:30.326 --> 18:31.675
OH, I, UH...

18:31.719 --> 18:35.114
UM, COME ON.
UM...

18:35.157 --> 18:37.203
OH!
OH. OKAY, THEN.

18:37.246 --> 18:39.988
Jerry: SAY, GRUDGEY,
WERE YOU AROUND TO TAXIDERMY

18:40.031 --> 18:41.337
ANY OF THOSE FISH
SWIMMING IN THE PIE HOLE

18:41.381 --> 18:43.122
WHEN THE RIVER BACKED UP?

18:43.165 --> 18:44.819
YOU TOLD THEM
ABOUT THAT, TOO?

18:44.862 --> 18:47.735
FISH ARE THE ONLY ANIMALS
I WON'T WORK ON.

18:47.778 --> 18:51.217
WHEN FISH DIE, THEY LOSE
ALL THE COLOR IN THEIR SKIN,

18:51.260 --> 18:54.698
AND AN ANIMAL'S COLOR
IS LIKE THEIR PERSONALITY.

18:54.742 --> 18:56.222
THAT'S SWEET.

18:56.265 --> 18:58.833
WHAT ELSE DID YOU TELL THEM
ABOUT THAT?

18:58.876 --> 19:01.401
SHE TOLD US WHEN THE WATER
STARTED RUSHING IN,

19:01.444 --> 19:02.924
YOU GOT TO GRABBING PIES
LIKE YOU BIRTHED 'EM.

19:02.967 --> 19:05.796
I THINK HE GRABBED
SOMETHING ELSE, TOO.

19:05.840 --> 19:07.581
THEY SAY
IN A TIME OF CRISIS,

19:07.624 --> 19:09.931
YOU GRAB THE THING
MOST IMPORTANT TO YOU.

19:09.974 --> 19:11.846
THAT'S WHAT I GRABBED.
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:11.889 --> 19:12.847
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:12.890 --> 19:14.196
[ SIREN WAILS ]

19:14.240 --> 19:15.589
OH, CRAP.

19:15.632 --> 19:18.069
ROAD TRIP INTERRUPTUS.

19:18.113 --> 19:19.549
WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

19:19.593 --> 19:21.508
HUH?

19:21.551 --> 19:23.379
WE HAVEN'T HAD
THIS MANY VISITORS

19:23.423 --> 19:25.468
SINCE OUR MOST RECENT
HOME INVASION.

19:25.512 --> 19:26.774
WE COULD REALLY USE
YOUR HELP.

19:26.817 --> 19:28.384
AND YOUR TAXIDERMY KIT.

19:28.428 --> 19:29.646
I HAD TO TAKE MINE
OUT OF THE VAN

19:29.690 --> 19:31.213
TO MAKE ROOM
FOR THE PASSENGERS.

19:31.257 --> 19:32.867
WHO'S DEAD?
NOBODY. WHAT A SILLY THING.

19:32.910 --> 19:34.434
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:34.477 --> 19:36.784
WE WERE THINKING MORE ALONG
THE LINES OF DISGUISE

19:36.827 --> 19:38.655
SO WE COULD GET PAST
THE ROADBLOCKS.

19:38.699 --> 19:40.744
I'M GONNA FASHION
THESE ALL-PURPOSE PATCH PELTS

19:40.788 --> 19:42.659
INTO MUTTONCHOPS
AND THE SUCH.

19:42.703 --> 19:45.488
AND THEY COULD REALLY USE
A CHANGE OF WARDROBE.

19:45.532 --> 19:47.751
THERE'S A TRUNK FULL OF
CHARLES CHARLES' OLD CLOTHES

19:47.795 --> 19:49.013
UPSTAIRS
IN THE CHEESE ROOM.

19:49.057 --> 19:50.885
Lily: HEY. UNH-UNH.

19:50.928 --> 19:53.409
THE ONLY THING THAT SMOKES
IN THIS HOUSE IS THE GOUDA.

19:53.453 --> 19:55.106
YOU WANT A CANCER-STICK,

19:55.150 --> 19:57.239
YOU STICK IT OUTSIDE
ON THE PORCH.

19:57.283 --> 19:59.546
THIS AIN'T QUITE THE PARTY
WE HAD IN MIND

19:59.589 --> 20:00.721
FOR YOU
AND THE WORRY WART.

20:00.764 --> 20:01.983
ENGAGEMENT?

20:02.026 --> 20:03.376
NED...

20:03.419 --> 20:04.594
AND OLIVE?

20:08.207 --> 20:09.773
Olive: OH.

20:09.817 --> 20:11.688
WHAT THE HELL
DO YOU MEAN "ENGAGED"?

20:11.732 --> 20:13.342
SINCE WHEN?
Ned: SINCE...

20:13.386 --> 20:16.171
WE LOVE EACH OTHER...
SO MUCH.

20:16.215 --> 20:17.172
[ Sighing ] OH.

20:17.216 --> 20:18.260
YEAH.

20:18.304 --> 20:19.870
WHAT HE SAID.

20:19.914 --> 20:20.958
[ CHUCKLES WEAKLY ]

20:26.355 --> 20:27.443
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:30.577 --> 20:33.536
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:33.580 --> 20:36.060
[ "HELLO" PLAYS ]

20:44.068 --> 20:50.118
♪ I'VE BEEN ALONE WITH YOU
INSIDE MY MIND ♪

20:50.161 --> 20:55.036
♪ AND IN MY DREAMS,
I'VE KISSED YOUR LIPS ♪

20:55.079 --> 20:58.518
♪ A THOUSAND TIMES

20:58.561 --> 21:04.132
♪ I SOMETIMES SEE YOU PASS
OUTSIDE MY DOOR ♪

21:06.221 --> 21:09.572
♪ HELLO

21:09.616 --> 21:13.097
♪ IS IT ME YOU'RE
LOOKING FOR? ♪

21:13.141 --> 21:16.275
♪ I CAN SEE IT IN YOUR EYES

21:16.318 --> 21:20.409
♪ I CAN SEE IT IN YOUR SMILE

21:20.453 --> 21:24.413
♪ YOU'RE ALL I'VE
EVER WANTED ♪

21:24.457 --> 21:27.677
♪ MY ARMS ARE OPEN WIDE

21:27.721 --> 21:32.073
♪ 'CAUSE YOU KNOW
JUST WHAT TO SAY ♪

21:32.116 --> 21:35.946
♪ AND YOU KNOW
JUST WHAT TO DO ♪

21:35.990 --> 21:37.948
DO YOU KNOW
JUST WHAT YOU'RE DOING?

21:37.992 --> 21:39.472
NOT REALLY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:39.515 --> 21:40.734
I ASKED MYSELF, "WHAT WOULD
OLIVE WANT ME TO DO?"

21:40.777 --> 21:42.388
AND THIS SEEMED LIKE
THE ANSWER.

21:42.431 --> 21:45.216
OH, YOU DID EXACTLY
WHAT I WOULD WANT YOU TO DO --

21:45.260 --> 21:48.219
ONLY, I'D ALSO WANT YOU
TO MEAN IT WHEN YOU
SAY YOU LOVE ME.

21:48.263 --> 21:49.656
NOT THAT I'M UNGRATEFUL.

21:49.699 --> 21:52.006
I DO MEAN IT --
IN A FRIEND WAY.

21:52.049 --> 21:53.399
AND I'M KIND OF
HAVING FUN.

21:53.442 --> 21:55.357
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

21:55.401 --> 21:57.446
I GET TO HELP YOU
IN A WAY THAT DOESN'T
REQUIRE BEING SUPER.

21:57.490 --> 22:01.363
IT JUST REQUIRES BEING NORMAL
AND A LITTLE DISHONEST.

22:01.407 --> 22:03.583
I KNOW YOU HAVE YOUR REASONS
FOR WRITING WHAT YOU WROTE

22:03.626 --> 22:05.802
IN THOSE LETTERS
TO BUSTER AND JERRY.

22:05.846 --> 22:10.154
AND I SUPPORT THEM,
BECAUSE I SUPPORT YOU.

22:10.198 --> 22:13.375
THAT'S WHAT FRIENDS DO.

22:13.419 --> 22:15.377
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

22:15.421 --> 22:18.380
Narrator:
THE PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR
AND THE ALIVE-AGAIN AVENGER

22:18.424 --> 22:20.426
RETURNED TO
DICKER'S DEPARTMENT STORE

22:20.469 --> 22:24.125
FOR THE UNVEILING OF THE ERIN
EMBRY MEMORIAL WINDOW,

22:24.168 --> 22:28.303
IN HOPES HER KILLER WOULD SOON
BE UNVEILED, AS WELL.

22:28.347 --> 22:29.957
THE CRAFT AND BEAUTY

22:30.000 --> 22:32.046
OF DICKER'S SIGNATURE
WINDOW DISPLAYS

22:32.089 --> 22:34.701
HAVE LONG BEEN ATTRIBUTED
TO TWO WOMEN --

22:34.744 --> 22:37.356
ONE OF WHOM,
DUE TO A TRAGIC ACCIDENT,

22:37.399 --> 22:38.835
IS NO LONGER WITH US.

22:38.879 --> 22:41.229
BUT BOTH, WE CELEBRATE TONIGHT

22:41.272 --> 22:44.885
AS WE UNVEIL THE ERIN EMBRY
MEMORIAL WINDOW,

22:44.928 --> 22:47.844
DESIGNED BY HER LONGTIME
DRESSING COMPANION,

22:47.888 --> 22:49.368
COCO JUNIPER.

22:49.411 --> 22:51.326
COCO?

22:51.370 --> 22:52.980
UH, COCO?

22:53.023 --> 22:54.721
[ DENNY CLEARS THROAT ]

22:54.764 --> 22:56.505
COCO WANTS TO GREET
HER GUESTS AND ADMIRERS

22:56.549 --> 22:58.464
AT THE COCKTAIL MEMORIAL
AFTER THE UNVEILING.

22:58.507 --> 23:01.249
WELL, THEN,
WITHOUT FURTHER ADO...

23:01.989 --> 23:03.294
[ BEEP ]

23:04.383 --> 23:06.602
[ CROWD GASPS ]

23:06.646 --> 23:08.212
[ APPLAUSE ]

23:12.521 --> 23:14.218
IT'S AN ESSAY
ON THE AFTERLIFE.

23:14.262 --> 23:17.439
ERIN EMBRY'S ENDLESS ASCENT
INTO A SPIRITUAL MAZE.

23:17.483 --> 23:20.224
LOOK AT IT.
IT'S...A BATH.

23:20.268 --> 23:22.444
IT'S JUST A WARM BATH.

23:22.488 --> 23:23.967
[ WOMAN SCREAMS ]

23:24.011 --> 23:25.795
[ CROWD MURMURING ]

23:25.839 --> 23:28.450
OH, MY GOD!

23:28.494 --> 23:29.886
Chuck: IT'S COCO!

23:29.930 --> 23:32.672
WELL, SAY GOODBYE
TO SUSPECT NUMERO UNO.

23:32.715 --> 23:34.543
AND HELLO,
VICTIM NUMERO DOS.

23:44.335 --> 23:45.859
Psst! HEY.

23:45.902 --> 23:47.991
HOW LONG YOU THINK
SHE BEEN DEAD?

23:48.035 --> 23:49.210
OH, I'D SAY ABOUT $50.

23:49.253 --> 23:50.254
[ GRUNTS ]

23:54.084 --> 23:55.129
SHE'S COLD,
BUT SHE AIN'T STIFF.

23:55.172 --> 23:56.870
NO MORE THAN 30 MINUTES.

23:56.913 --> 23:59.220
EXACT TIME WILL TAKE ME
A LITTLE CONDUCTING...

23:59.263 --> 24:00.482
AND ANOTHER $20.

24:00.526 --> 24:02.441
"30 MINUTES" WILL DO.
THANK YOU.

24:02.484 --> 24:04.181
OH, THAT'S HOW IT IS?

24:04.225 --> 24:07.141
WELL, THEN, I'LL MAKE
A...MENTAL NOTE ON THAT.

24:07.184 --> 24:08.664
DON'T BE MAKING
NO MENTAL NOTES ON ME.

24:08.708 --> 24:10.927
AT A CRIME SCENE,
I MAKE MENTAL NOTES

24:10.971 --> 24:13.103
ON WHATEVER I FEEL
NEEDS NOTE-MAKIN'...

24:13.147 --> 24:15.236
MENTALLY.

24:15.279 --> 24:16.498
♪ DICKER'S

24:16.542 --> 24:18.544
IT WAS MY DREAM
TO WORK WITH ERIN

24:18.587 --> 24:21.329
AND, TO A LESSER
EXTENT, COCO.

24:21.372 --> 24:22.896
NOW THEY'RE BOTH GONE,

24:22.939 --> 24:25.681
AND MY DREAM
TO MINE THE CREATIVE MINDS

24:25.725 --> 24:29.729
THAT FED MY CREATIVE SOUL
WILL FOREVER REMAIN A FANTASY.

24:29.772 --> 24:32.427
THE WINDOWS
FED YOUR CREATIVE SOUL?

24:32.471 --> 24:34.647
Chuck:
I AM SO SORRY, DENNY.

24:34.690 --> 24:36.649
I MEAN, FIRST ERIN
AND NOW COCO.

24:36.692 --> 24:38.041
I CAN'T IMAGINE
HOW YOU MUST FEEL.

24:38.085 --> 24:40.174
LIKE A WEIGHT
HAS BEEN LIFTED.

24:44.657 --> 24:47.355
HIS HONESTY TILTS
A LITTLE TOWARD

24:47.398 --> 24:49.705
THE "I DON'T CARE
THAT THEY DIED" TERRITORY.

24:49.749 --> 24:51.838
"TILTS"? HIS HONESTLY
FALLS RIGHT INTO

24:51.881 --> 24:54.580
THE "I KILLED BOTH OF THEM
SKANKS" SIDE OF THINGS.

24:54.623 --> 24:57.408
THE STORE WAS CLOSED
WHILE COCO FINISHED
DRESSING THAT WINDOW,

24:57.452 --> 24:59.715
WHICH MEANS SHE WAS DEAD
BEFORE THE PUBLIC SAW IT.

24:59.759 --> 25:01.761
BUT NOT BEFORE
"CHIC AS HELL" DENNY SAW IT.

25:01.804 --> 25:03.414
HE KNEW THAT COCO
WAS GONNA BE INSIDE,

25:03.458 --> 25:05.155
WAITING TO BE GREETED
AT THE MEMORIAL,

25:05.199 --> 25:07.680
BECAUSE INSIDE
IS WHERE HE KILLED HER.

25:07.723 --> 25:09.508
MM-HMM.

25:09.551 --> 25:12.641
TIME TO TAKE ANOTHER VISIT
TO ERIN AND COCO'S WORKSPACE,

25:12.685 --> 25:14.861
SEE WHAT OLD DENNY'S
BEEN UP TO.

25:14.904 --> 25:16.166
[ Gruff voice ] YEAH.

25:16.210 --> 25:19.605
YEAH.
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

25:19.648 --> 25:21.302
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU SAVED

25:21.345 --> 25:23.696
ALL OF CHARLES CHARLES'
OLD CLOTHES.

25:23.739 --> 25:26.176
I WAS GONNA USE THE FABRIC
TO MAKE A QUILT FOR CHARLOTTE,

25:26.220 --> 25:27.700
BUT LILY SAID
THAT WAS MORBID.

25:27.743 --> 25:29.876
I COULDN'T BRING MYSELF
TO THROW THEM AWAY.

25:29.919 --> 25:32.313
I'M A PACK RAT OF
SORTS MYSELF --

25:32.356 --> 25:35.403
OF EMOTIONS, NOT SO MUCH
WITH ACTUAL THINGS.

25:35.446 --> 25:36.926
IS THAT WHY
YOU PREVIOUSLY DENIED

25:36.970 --> 25:38.319
YOUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH NED?

25:38.362 --> 25:41.365
OH. ABOUT THAT --
I SHOULD PRO-O-O...

25:41.409 --> 25:42.584
IT'S THE VEIL I WAS TO WEAR

25:42.628 --> 25:43.890
WHEN CHARLES
AND I GOT MARRIED.

25:43.933 --> 25:45.021
THE SON OF A BITCH.

25:45.065 --> 25:47.023
HOLY MATRIMONY.

25:47.067 --> 25:49.809
I HAD HOPED CHARLOTTE
MIGHT WEAR IT SOMEDAY.

25:49.852 --> 25:52.638
THE NEWS OF YOUR ENGAGEMENT
HAS RESTORED IN ME A FAITH

25:52.681 --> 25:55.554
THAT TRUE LOVE EXISTS
FOR PEOPLE WHO DESERVE IT.

25:56.642 --> 25:58.382
THAT'S SO DEPRESSING.

25:58.426 --> 26:00.950
YOU'VE GIVEN ME SOMETHING
TO BELIEVE IN,

26:00.994 --> 26:03.257
LIKE THE LIKENESS OF THE
VIRGIN MARY FOUND INGRAINED

26:03.300 --> 26:05.520
IN THE CENTER OF A
POTATO OR TORTILLA.

26:05.564 --> 26:09.219
RIGHT NOW, YOU AND NED
ARE MY TORTILLA.

26:09.263 --> 26:10.917
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:10.960 --> 26:13.354
Narrator: OLIVE COULDN'T
BRING HERSELF TO DISAVOW

26:13.397 --> 26:15.835
VIVIAN'S RESTORED
BELIEF IN VOWS,

26:15.878 --> 26:18.838
SO, INSTEAD,
SHE SIMPLY SAID...

26:18.881 --> 26:20.709
THANKS.
[ SIGHS ]

26:20.753 --> 26:21.928
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

26:29.109 --> 26:30.458
Alright.

26:33.940 --> 26:35.376
LOOK AT THAT.

26:35.419 --> 26:38.945
NOT A PEN, NOT A PAPER CLIP,
NOT NO THING.

26:38.988 --> 26:41.730
THESE PEOPLE DIDN'T DO
A DAMN THING FOR THEMSELVES.

26:41.774 --> 26:44.037
THEY DIDN'T HAVE TO -- NOT
WHEN THEY HAD SOMEONE ELSE
DOING EVERYTHING FOR THEM.

26:44.080 --> 26:45.865
[ SIGHS ]

26:45.908 --> 26:47.388
I WONDER WHAT OLIVE'S DOING
FOR NED RIGHT NOW.

26:47.431 --> 26:49.259
MM-HMM.

26:49.303 --> 26:50.652
THINK YOU CAN
POUR A SAUCER OF MILK

26:50.696 --> 26:52.262
AND SEE
IF KITTY WILL SPLASH?

26:52.306 --> 26:54.874
THIS AIN'T MY MILK, AND I
AIN'T DIPPING MY PAW IN IT.

26:54.917 --> 26:57.093
I'M NOT BEING CATTY.
I'M BEING CONCERNED.

26:57.137 --> 27:00.270
YOU SAID A LOT CAN HAPPEN
IN ONE DAY.

27:00.314 --> 27:01.924
AND YOU KNOW WHAT YOU WERE
DOING WHEN YOU SAID THAT?

27:01.968 --> 27:04.231
YEAH, I KNOW --
DIPPING MY PAW.

27:04.274 --> 27:07.538
I MEAN, WHAT HAPPENS IF OLIVE
HOLDS HIS HAND WITHOUT GLOVES

27:07.582 --> 27:10.890
OR KISSES HIM WITHOUT USING
PLASTIC FOOD WRAP?

27:10.933 --> 27:13.240
HE'LL KNOW WHAT HE WAS
MISSING WITH ME.

27:13.283 --> 27:15.808
THE ONLY THING PIE-MAN
IS GONNA BE MISSING IS YOU.

27:15.851 --> 27:17.853
HE'S ALWAYS FRETTING
YOU'RE GONNA GET UP AND GO,

27:17.897 --> 27:19.942
AND HERE YOU ARE, WORRIED
THAT HE GOT UP AND WENT.

27:19.986 --> 27:22.771
I'M TELLING YOU,
AIN'T NOBODY GOIN' NOWHERE.

27:22.815 --> 27:24.033
MOVE.

27:24.077 --> 27:26.035
OH! BOOYAH!

27:26.079 --> 27:29.125
DENNY'S BOOK!

27:29.169 --> 27:32.041
AND ALL THE ARTISTIC
RENDERINGS

27:32.085 --> 27:36.742
OF COCO AND ERIN'S WINDOWS
HERE AT DICKER'S.

27:36.785 --> 27:39.570
COCO AND ERIN DIDN'T DESIGN
ANY OF THESE WINDOWS.

27:39.614 --> 27:41.572
"CHIC AS HELL" DENNY DID.

27:41.616 --> 27:44.053
PEOPLE WHO NEED PEOPLE TO DO
EVERY DAMN THING FOR THEM

27:44.097 --> 27:46.273
AREN'T ALWAYS THE LUCKIEST
PEOPLE IN THE WORLD.

27:46.316 --> 27:48.362
SOMETIMES THOSE PEEPS
GET PISSED OFF

27:48.405 --> 27:50.103
AND START RESENTING
THEIR LAZY-ASS BOSSES.

27:50.146 --> 27:53.062
ERIN AND COCO'S PEEP DONE GONE
POSTAL AND KILLED BOTH OF 'EM.

27:53.106 --> 27:54.585
PEEP THIS, PLAYA.

27:54.629 --> 27:56.022
DON'T DO THAT. SORRY.

27:56.065 --> 27:58.285
THAT LOOKS AN AWFUL LOT
LIKE DICK DICKER.

27:58.328 --> 28:02.115
OH, WE BETTER FIND DICK
BEFORE THIS PISSED-OFF
PEEP POPS HIM NEXT.

28:02.158 --> 28:03.507
COME ON.

28:03.551 --> 28:05.988
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

28:06.032 --> 28:07.729
Ned!

28:07.773 --> 28:09.688
I NEVER THOUGHT
I'D SAY THIS,

28:09.731 --> 28:11.602
BUT WE NEED TO BACK OFF
ON THE PDA,

28:11.646 --> 28:13.692
'CAUSE VIVIAN'S P's AND Q's
HAVE GONE A-W-O-L,

28:13.735 --> 28:16.433
AND I CAN'T TAKE MUCH
MORE OF WHAT I JUST TOOK
BEFORE I'M D.O.A.

28:16.477 --> 28:18.174
OLIVE...
USE YOUR WORDS.

28:18.218 --> 28:20.611
OR YOUR VEIL.
USE YOUR VEIL.

28:20.655 --> 28:22.309
YOUR -- YOUR WEDDING VEIL.
YOU HAVE A WEDDING VEIL.

28:22.352 --> 28:23.614
WHY DO YOU HAVE
A WEDDING VEIL?

28:23.658 --> 28:24.877
WE'RE STILL JUST
PLAYING, RIGHT?

28:24.920 --> 28:26.835
VIVIAN'S JUMPED
THE BRIDAL SHARK,

28:26.879 --> 28:28.054
AND UNLESS
YOU'RE ACTUALLY PLANNING

28:28.097 --> 28:30.143
ON SAYING "I DO"
AT SOME POINT,

28:30.186 --> 28:32.536
WE'RE GONNA HAVE ENOUGH
EXPLAINING TO DO BEFORE
WE CALL IT ALL OFF.

28:32.580 --> 28:35.278
NED, I REALLY APPRECIATE YOU
GOING ALONG WITH ALL OF THIS.

28:35.322 --> 28:36.845
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
THANK ME.

28:36.889 --> 28:39.674
I'VE BEEN CURIOUS ABOUT HAVING
A NORMAL RELATIONSHIP.

28:39.718 --> 28:42.895
THIS ONE'S BEEN REALLY
INTERESTING TO TRY ON.

28:42.938 --> 28:44.070
"TRY ON"?

28:44.113 --> 28:46.681
YOU TRY ON A SWEATER
AT THE MALL.

28:46.725 --> 28:49.292
YOU TRY YOUR BEST FRIEND'S
BRA, AND SMILE ON THE INSIDE

28:49.336 --> 28:50.685
'CAUSE YOURS
ARE BIGGER AND BETTER.

28:50.729 --> 28:52.469
YOU DON'T TRY ON
A PERSON.

28:52.513 --> 28:54.384
CLEARLY NOT
THE RIGHT CHOICE OF WORDS.

28:54.428 --> 28:58.301
IS THAT WHAT "WELL, I WOULDN'T
SAY 'NEVER'" WAS ALL ABOUT?

28:58.345 --> 29:00.434
WERE YOU TRYING ME ON
IN YOUR HEAD?!

29:00.477 --> 29:02.828
UH...UM...I DO--

29:02.871 --> 29:04.699
I DON'T KNOW WHAT WORDS
TO CHOOSE NOW.

29:04.743 --> 29:07.223
OH, I DO!

29:07.267 --> 29:10.183
LISTEN UP, 'CAUSE I'M ONLY
GONNA SAY THIS ONCE.

29:10.226 --> 29:12.838
FIRST AND FOREMOST,
I'M SORRY,

29:12.881 --> 29:14.927
BOTH FOR
WHAT I'M ABOUT TO TELL YOU

29:14.970 --> 29:16.842
AND THE HYSTERIA WITH WHICH
I'M ABOUT TO TELL IT,

29:16.885 --> 29:19.540
WHICH IS IN NO WAY DIRECTED
AT ANY OF YOU,

29:19.583 --> 29:22.064
NOR IS IT RELATED
TO A FEMALE ISSUE OF ANY KIND.

29:23.979 --> 29:26.373
NED IS NOT MY FIANCE.

29:26.416 --> 29:28.462
HE DOES NOT LOVE ME.

29:28.505 --> 29:30.507
WE ARE NOT A COUPLE --
NEVER HAVE BEEN.

29:30.551 --> 29:34.294
I LOVE HIM, BUT...
HE NEVER HAD FEELINGS FOR ME.

29:34.337 --> 29:35.686
WELL...

29:35.730 --> 29:38.385
I WOULDN'T SAY "NEVER."

29:38.428 --> 29:41.040
[ Voice breaking ]
I'M SO SORRY.

29:41.083 --> 29:42.432
I AIN'T MAD AT YA.

29:44.086 --> 29:47.176
TAKE "MAD" AND MULTIPLY THAT
BY A POWER OF "PISSED."

29:47.220 --> 29:49.831
DON'T BE MAD -- AND
CERTAINLY NOT TO A
POWER OF THAT DEGREE.

29:49.875 --> 29:52.529
I LOVE OLIVE...

29:52.573 --> 29:54.705
AS A FRIEND.

29:54.749 --> 29:56.620
I THINK YOU PROBABLY
SHOULD JUST GO.

29:56.664 --> 29:58.753
I DIDN'T MEAN --

29:58.797 --> 30:00.537
OLIVE,
I JUST WANTED TO HELP.

30:00.581 --> 30:04.063
I KNOW, BUT I DON'T WANT
THAT KIND OF HELP.

30:04.106 --> 30:05.934
"TRY ON" TIME'S
OVER, NED.

30:09.068 --> 30:10.069
I'M SORRY.

30:18.817 --> 30:21.341
I CAN'T GO.

30:21.384 --> 30:24.518
Policeman:
[ Amplified ] JERRY HOLMES
AND BUSTER BUSTAMANTE.

30:24.561 --> 30:26.128
WE HAVE YOU SURROUNDED.

30:26.172 --> 30:28.174
SURRENDER AND COME OUT
WITH YOUR HANDS UP.

30:32.743 --> 30:34.310
Policeman: RELEASE THE
HOSTAGES AND SURRENDER NOW.

30:34.354 --> 30:36.486
THE NEWSMAN ON THE RADIO
LAUDED THE CONCERNED NEIGHBOR

30:36.530 --> 30:38.184
WHO REPORTED
THE TWO GENTLEMEN

30:38.227 --> 30:40.447
WHO MATCHED THE DESCRIPTION OF
THE RECENTLY ESCAPED PRISONERS

30:40.490 --> 30:42.928
AFTER SEEING...THEM ON OUR
PORCH SMOKING CIGARETTES.

30:45.060 --> 30:46.192
WELL,
IT'S A FILTHY HABIT.

30:46.235 --> 30:48.411
WE CAN'T GO BACK,
SNOOK.

30:48.455 --> 30:50.936
YOU'RE NOT GOING BACK.
I PROMISE.

30:50.979 --> 30:53.155
FINE MESS
WE'VE GOTTEN YOU INTO, HUH?

30:53.199 --> 30:56.289
OH, I DO MY FAIR SHARE
OF MAKING MESSES, TOO.

30:56.332 --> 30:57.899
YOU'RE THE SAME
9-YEAR-OLD LITTLE GIRL

30:57.943 --> 31:00.380
WHO CLIMBED INTO THE BACKSEAT
OF OUR GETAWAY CAR,

31:00.423 --> 31:03.035
DOING ASS-OVER-TEA KETTLE
CRAZY THINGS

31:03.078 --> 31:05.907
JUST TO GET PEOPLE
TO PAY ATTENTION TO YOU.

31:05.951 --> 31:09.606
Narrator:
WHILE OLIVE PONDERED HOW
EVERYTHING HAD GONE SO WRONG,

31:09.650 --> 31:12.566
THE PIE MAKER TRIED TO FIGURE
HOW HE COULD MAKE IT RIGHT.

31:12.609 --> 31:15.525
I ONLY DID WHAT I THOUGHT
SHE'D WANT ME TO DO.

31:15.569 --> 31:17.049
I THOUGHT I'D BE HELPFUL

31:17.092 --> 31:19.138
BY PRETENDING TO BE NORMAL
AND NOT SUPER.

31:19.181 --> 31:22.445
CLARK KENT NEVER HAD THIS MUCH
TROUBLE WITH RELATIONSHIPS.

31:22.489 --> 31:23.969
THAT'S BECAUSE
HE DIDN'T HAVE ANY.

31:24.012 --> 31:25.144
SURE HE DID.

31:25.187 --> 31:26.188
NO, HE DIDN'T.

31:26.232 --> 31:27.581
I MEAN, SUPERMAN DID.

31:27.624 --> 31:29.583
NOBODY GAVE A CRAP
ABOUT CLARK KENT.

31:29.626 --> 31:31.715
HE COULD DISAPPEAR OFF THE
FACE OF THE DAILY PLANET

31:31.759 --> 31:33.021
AND NOBODY WOULD
EVEN NOTICE.

31:33.065 --> 31:34.544
BUT I BET
HE'D SPIT SPANDEX

31:34.588 --> 31:36.459
TO FIND SOMEONE
SPECIAL ENOUGH

31:36.503 --> 31:38.679
WHO CARED ABOUT THE MAN
AND NOT THE CAPE.

31:38.722 --> 31:40.637
Narrator: THE PIE MAKER
LOOKED AT OLIVE,

31:40.681 --> 31:42.509
THE PERSON WHO CARED
FOR THE MAN

31:42.552 --> 31:44.337
AND KNEW NOTHING OF THE CAPE,

31:44.380 --> 31:47.818
AND SILENTLY WISHED
FOR SPANDEX SALIVA.

31:47.862 --> 31:50.386
BUT IF LOIS OR MR. WHITE
OR JIMMY OLSEN

31:50.430 --> 31:52.954
FOUND OUT THAT CLARK AND
SUPERMAN WERE ONE IN THE SAME,

31:52.998 --> 31:55.435
THEN CLARK WOULD BE
MORE STUDLY AND COOL,

31:55.478 --> 31:58.307
BUT ON HIS OWN, HE'S JUST
A SUPER-TALL CLUMSY GUY

31:58.351 --> 32:00.092
CRAMMING HIMSELF
INTO A PHONE BOOTH.

32:00.135 --> 32:03.443
IF YOU WERE CLARK KENT,
WHAT WOULD YOU DO RIGHT NOW?

32:03.486 --> 32:07.055
I WOULD RIP OFF MY SHIRT
AND BECOME SUPERMAN.

32:07.099 --> 32:08.970
I MEAN, COME ON.

32:09.014 --> 32:12.234
PEOPLE THAT HAVE SUPERPOWERS
DON'T NOT WANT TO USE THEM.

32:16.456 --> 32:17.936
Randy:
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

32:17.979 --> 32:19.546
TO PUT ON MY CAPE.

32:22.853 --> 32:25.160
Narrator: EMERSON COD
AND HIS SIDEKICK, CHUCK,

32:25.204 --> 32:27.467
FOUND DICK DICKER
TO FOREWARN HIM

32:27.510 --> 32:29.338
DENNY DOWNS HAD GONE DEMENTED.

32:29.382 --> 32:31.732
WE BELIEVE DENNY DOWNS
HAS GONE DEMENTED.

32:31.775 --> 32:35.257
DENNY DESIGNED THE WINDOWS?
WHAT WERE ERIN AND COCO DOING?

32:35.301 --> 32:37.607
TAKING THE CREDIT.

32:37.651 --> 32:39.479
HE GOT FED UP WITH DOING
ALL THE WORK AND GETTING
NONE OF THE GLORY.

32:39.522 --> 32:41.133
YOU'RE ANOTHER BOSS
HE BLAMES.

32:41.176 --> 32:44.745
LOOKS LIKE YOU'RE MEANT TO BE
HIS WINDOW-WHACKING FINALE.

32:44.788 --> 32:46.790
DENNY'S BEEN PART OF
THE DICKER'S FAMILY FOR YEARS.

32:46.834 --> 32:49.228
I CAN'T BELIEVE
WHAT YOU'RE TELLING ME.

32:49.271 --> 32:52.187
I NEED A DRINK.
WOULD YOU LIKE A DRINK?

32:52.231 --> 32:54.276
WELL, I WOULDN'T SAY NO
TO A SNORT.

32:54.320 --> 32:56.104
[ SNIFFS ]
SCOTCH, PLEASE.

32:56.148 --> 32:57.758
OH. I'M OUT OF SCOTCH.

32:57.801 --> 33:00.326
BUT I MAKE THE MOST
DIVINE POMEGRANA-TINI

33:00.369 --> 33:01.457
THAT'LL EVER PASS
YOUR LIPS.

33:01.501 --> 33:03.198
YUM! YUM.

33:03.242 --> 33:05.026
NOW, WE'VE NOTIFIED
THE AUTHORITIES,

33:05.070 --> 33:06.854
BUT THEY STILL DON'T SEEM
TO BE ABLE TO LOCATE DENNY.

33:06.897 --> 33:08.421
HE'S ON THE LOOSE?

33:08.464 --> 33:10.031
I'LL NEED
A PROPER BODYGUARD.

33:10.075 --> 33:11.467
SAMSON, MY DRIVER,

33:11.511 --> 33:13.600
WOULD USE ME AS A HUMAN SHIELD
IN A HEARTBEAT

33:13.643 --> 33:15.689
IF THERE WAS EVEN
THE VAGUEST NOTION OF THREAT.

33:15.732 --> 33:17.038
WHAT DO I DO?

33:17.082 --> 33:18.692
GET THEE
TO A POLICE STATION.

33:18.735 --> 33:21.390
WE'LL GET WE TO THE MORGUE
TO GET THE CORONER'S REPORT

33:21.434 --> 33:23.001
AND SEE IF THE SCIENCE
OF THE DEAD

33:23.044 --> 33:24.567
MATCHES THE THEORY
IN MY HEAD.

33:24.611 --> 33:26.874
Narrator: WHILE THE PRIVATE
INVESTIGATOR AND AVENGER

33:26.917 --> 33:30.443
ADVISED DICK DICKER
TO SEEK THE POLICE...

33:30.486 --> 33:34.186
THE PIE MAKER WAS TRYING
TO AVOID THEM.

33:34.229 --> 33:35.535
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

33:42.194 --> 33:43.586
[ CLATTERING ]

33:43.630 --> 33:44.631
[ GUNS COCK ]

33:44.674 --> 33:46.111
[ CLATTERING CONTINUES ]

33:57.948 --> 33:59.124
[ CLATTER ]

33:59.167 --> 34:00.473
[ CREATURE GROWLS ]

34:00.516 --> 34:02.866
AAH! RHINO!

34:02.910 --> 34:05.391
[ ALL SCREAMING ]

34:05.434 --> 34:06.870
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

34:06.914 --> 34:08.350
HEY-HO, RHINO!

34:08.394 --> 34:10.265
I thought he was dead.
Me too!

34:10.309 --> 34:14.791
[ SIREN WAILS, TIRES SCREECH ]

34:14.835 --> 34:17.577
FASTER THAN A SPEEDING BULLET.

34:17.620 --> 34:19.709
GO, GO!
[ GASPS ]

34:19.753 --> 34:20.797
OH!

34:20.841 --> 34:22.103
[ RHINO GROWLING ]

34:26.586 --> 34:27.804
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

34:32.766 --> 34:34.072
I'M GOING TO BED.

34:38.815 --> 34:40.513
Narrator: THE PIE MAKER
HELPED HIS FRIENDS IN NEED --

34:40.556 --> 34:43.472
NOT BY PRETENDING
HE WAS SOMETHING HE WAS NOT,

34:43.516 --> 34:47.302
BUT BY EMBRACING THE VERY
THING HE ALWAYS WAS.

34:47.346 --> 34:50.218
IT GAVE HIM A FEELING OF JOY
HE WOULD LATER LIKEN

34:50.262 --> 34:53.830
TO LEAPING TALL BUILDINGS
IN A SINGLE BOUND.

34:57.486 --> 34:58.922
HMM.

34:58.966 --> 35:01.447
THE INDENTATION OF THE DENT
IN ERIN'S DOME

35:01.490 --> 35:03.275
LOOKS A HELL OF A LOT LIKE
THE CRYSTAL LIQUOR DECANTERS

35:03.318 --> 35:04.928
IN DICK'S LIMO.

35:04.972 --> 35:07.148
DO YOU THINK THAT DENNY WAS
TRYING TO FRAME DICK DICKER?

35:07.192 --> 35:08.410
DENNY AIN'T THE KILLER.

35:10.586 --> 35:12.675
I'M SUPERMAN. I'VE GOT A FINGER
FASTER THAN A SPEEDING BULLET.

35:12.719 --> 35:14.721
COME ON.
WHO CAN I TOUCH?

35:14.764 --> 35:16.244
NED, YOU'RE TOUCHING
DEAD THINGS AGAIN?

35:16.288 --> 35:18.028
UH, NO MORE
PRETENDING TO BE NORMAL.

35:18.072 --> 35:19.334
THE BEST WAY
I CAN HELP ANYONE

35:19.378 --> 35:21.206
IS BY BEING
A PIE-MAKING DEAD-WAKER.

35:21.249 --> 35:24.209
PRETENDING TO BE SOMETHING I'M
NOT IS A RECIPE FOR DISASTER.

35:24.252 --> 35:27.995
SO, I SAY YES TO "SUPER"
AND NO TO "NORMAL."

35:28.038 --> 35:30.084
IF CAPED CRUSADER REALLY IS
BACK IN THE SUPER SADDLE,

35:30.128 --> 35:33.392
TOUCH THESE DICKER DAMES
AND PROVE ME RIGHT.

35:33.435 --> 35:34.654
[ WATCH TICKING ]

35:34.697 --> 35:35.655
HELLO.

35:35.698 --> 35:37.700
HELLO.

35:37.744 --> 35:39.180
I'M VERY HAPPY TO TELL
YOU THAT ME BEING A
PIE-MAKING DEAD-WAKER

35:39.224 --> 35:40.399
GIVES US EXACTLY ONE MINUTE
TO HELP YOU HELP US

35:40.442 --> 35:42.227
BY CONFIRMING
MY PARTNER'S THEORY.

35:42.270 --> 35:44.142
DID DICK DICKER DO YOU IN
WHEN HE BRAINED YOU

35:44.185 --> 35:46.448
WITH THE CRYSTAL STOPPER
OF HIS DECANTER?

35:46.492 --> 35:48.058
YES!

35:48.102 --> 35:49.669
HE POURED ME A SCOTCH, SAID
MY WORK WAS AN INSPIRATION,

35:49.712 --> 35:51.192
AND STARTED BEATING ME
TO DEATH!

35:51.236 --> 35:53.325
HE SAID THAT THE
STORE GOING UNDER

35:53.368 --> 35:54.674
WAS THE ONLY WAY TO GET OUT
OF THE FAMILY BUSINESS

35:54.717 --> 35:56.806
AND STILL STAY
IN THE FAMILY.

35:56.850 --> 35:58.460
BEING THE TRUE TALENT
BEHIND THE WINDOWS,

35:58.504 --> 36:01.071
DICK SAID I HAD TO DIE BECAUSE
I BROUGHT ALL THE CUSTOMERS.

36:01.115 --> 36:02.377
YOU?

36:02.421 --> 36:04.249
IF I HAD LEGS,
I WOULD KICK YOUR ASS!

36:04.292 --> 36:05.989
WHERE ARE
YOUR LEGS?

36:06.033 --> 36:07.687
[ SCOFFS ] DICK FED ME
TO THE ESCALATOR

36:07.730 --> 36:09.950
AFTER RANTING LIKE A SIZE 10
AT A SAMPLE SALE.

36:09.993 --> 36:12.213
HE SAID HE WAS WRONG ABOUT YOU
AND IT WAS ACTUALLY MY WORK

36:12.257 --> 36:13.954
THAT BROUGHT IN
ALL THE CUSTOMERS.

36:13.997 --> 36:15.390
WELL, WITHOUT
BOTH OF Y'ALL'S WINDOWS

36:15.434 --> 36:16.826
BRINGING BUSINESS
INTO THE STORE,

36:16.870 --> 36:18.393
DICKER'S WOULD HAVE
HIT THE SKIDS.

36:18.437 --> 36:19.916
TIME'S UP!

36:19.960 --> 36:21.788
NO, I DON'T -- NO --
OH!

36:21.831 --> 36:23.920
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

36:23.964 --> 36:25.400
IF DICK WAS WILLING
TO KILL HIS DESIGNERS

36:25.444 --> 36:27.359
TO MAKE SURE
THAT THE STORE WOULD GO DOWN

36:27.402 --> 36:29.752
AND NOW HE KNOWS THAT DENNY IS
THE REAL DESIGNER...

36:29.796 --> 36:32.668
DENNY'S ABOUT TO BE
DAMNED WITH PRAISE.

36:32.712 --> 36:35.236
[ CHAIN SAW REVVING ]

36:35.280 --> 36:36.542
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE...

36:36.585 --> 36:38.108
FREEZE!
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

36:38.152 --> 36:39.806
Narrator: ...DICK DICKER
HAD A DESPERATE DESIRE

36:39.849 --> 36:42.504
TO BE RID OF THE FAMILY
THAT OWNED THE FAMILY STORE,

36:42.548 --> 36:45.420
BUT HE DID NOT WANT
TO BE DISOWNED.

36:45.464 --> 36:47.117
THE FANTASTICAL WINDOWS

36:47.161 --> 36:49.511
CREATED BY ERIN EMBRY
AND COCO JUNIPER

36:49.555 --> 36:51.383
BROUGHT CUSTOMERS IN.

36:51.426 --> 36:54.255
SO DICK DECIDED TO ELIMINATE
WHO HE BELIEVED

36:54.299 --> 36:57.476
TO BE THE TALENTED MEMBER
OF THE TEAM.

36:57.519 --> 37:00.435
ONLY TO DISCOVER,
ONCE THE DEED WAS DONE,

37:00.479 --> 37:04.352
THAT ERIN WASN'T THE ONE
WITH TALENT.

37:04.396 --> 37:06.398
DICK PENNED A SUICIDE NOTE,

37:06.441 --> 37:08.051
CLAIMING CREDIT
FOR THE MURDERS

37:08.095 --> 37:10.053
OF ERIN EMBRY AND COCO JUNIPER,

37:10.097 --> 37:13.709
SIGNED IT "DENNY DOWNS,"
AND PREPARED TO STRIKE.

37:13.753 --> 37:15.885
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

37:15.929 --> 37:18.236
DEBBIE DICKER BECAME
THE NEW PROPRIETRESS

37:18.279 --> 37:19.933
OF DICKER'S DEPARTMENT STORE.

37:19.976 --> 37:23.371
SHE PROMOTED DENNY DOWNS
TO HEAD WINDOW DESIGNER,

37:23.415 --> 37:26.244
WHO, IN TURN,
APPOINTED WENDELL FEATHERSTONE

37:26.287 --> 37:28.158
AS HIS NEW APPRENTICE.

37:28.202 --> 37:29.290
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

37:29.334 --> 37:31.423
NED DOESN'T LOVE ME.

37:31.466 --> 37:35.296
HE'S WITH SOMEONE ELSE
HE LOVES VERY MUCH.

37:35.340 --> 37:38.734
HEAR ME AND HEAR ME GOOD,
LITTLE GIRL.

37:38.778 --> 37:42.782
THE GUY WHO LOVES YOU --
WHO REALLY LOVES YOU --

37:42.825 --> 37:46.438
YOU WON'T EVER HAVE TO WONDER
HOW HE FEELS ABOUT YOU.

37:46.481 --> 37:49.789
YOU WILL FEEL IT WITH EVERY
INCH OF THE 59 YOU GOT.

37:49.832 --> 37:51.399
The Grudge up there

37:51.443 --> 37:54.707
has been truckin'
our sorry situation

37:54.750 --> 37:58.363
without a peep of
"What for?" or "How come?"

37:58.406 --> 38:00.278
And he ain't doin' it
for his health.

38:07.197 --> 38:08.721
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

38:08.764 --> 38:10.026
OH!

38:10.070 --> 38:12.202
HIYA.
HI.

38:12.246 --> 38:14.204
I'M REAL SORRY
ABOUT YOUR RHINOCEROS.

38:14.248 --> 38:19.209
CAN'T GO CRYING
OVER SPILLED RHINOCEROS...ES.

38:19.253 --> 38:22.952
ALTHOUGH I AM MORTIFIED
THAT ALOISIUS WAS STILL ALIVE.

38:22.996 --> 38:24.432
THAT IS NOT
THE KIND OF THING

38:24.476 --> 38:27.566
A TAXIDERMIST
SHOULD EVER OVERLOOK.

38:27.609 --> 38:30.264
WELL, I'VE BEEN DOING
SOME OVERLOOKING MYSELF.

38:30.308 --> 38:32.092
I WANTED TO THANK YOU,
RANDY MANN.

38:32.135 --> 38:34.094
DON'T MENTION IT,
MISS OLIVE.

38:34.137 --> 38:35.922
I'D AID AND ABET YOU
ANY TIME.

38:35.965 --> 38:37.576
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

38:37.619 --> 38:40.361
UH, BUT JUST SO
I DON'T GET CONFUSED AGAIN,

38:40.405 --> 38:43.277
YOU AND THE PIE-BRO
ARE OR ARE NOT ENGAGED?

38:43.321 --> 38:46.933
THE ONLY THING WE WERE
ENGAGED IN WAS SHENANIGANS.

38:46.976 --> 38:48.804
SHENANIGANS THAT COULD PUT
BUSTER AND JERRY

38:48.848 --> 38:50.197
BACK IN THE BIG HOUSE

38:50.240 --> 38:52.373
UNLESS WE GET THEM
ACROSS THE BORDER.

38:52.417 --> 38:53.896
BUT I DON'T KNOW HOW.

38:53.940 --> 38:57.378
WELL, I AM NOT ABOVE PRAYER.

38:57.422 --> 38:59.511
WHEN I WAS IN THE NUNNERY,
MOTHER SUPERIOR SAID

38:59.554 --> 39:02.209
PRAYER WAS JUST
REACHING OUT YOUR HANDS,

39:02.252 --> 39:05.430
KNOWING THE GOOD LORD
WAS REACHING BACK.

39:05.473 --> 39:08.346
WHO WOULD MOTHER SUPERIOR
TELL YOU TO REACH OUT TO NOW?

39:11.740 --> 39:12.959
I'M REACHING OUT TO YOU.

39:13.002 --> 39:15.396
BUSTER AND JERRY
SERVED THEIR TIME --

39:15.440 --> 39:16.745
WELL, MOST OF IT,
ANYWAY --

39:16.789 --> 39:19.226
BUT THEY SHOULD HAVE
SERVED NONE OF IT,

39:19.269 --> 39:21.141
SINCE THEY WERE
WRONGFULLY ACCUSED.

39:21.184 --> 39:23.361
THE WRONGFULLY ACCUSED
ARE NOT GUILTY

39:23.404 --> 39:25.406
IN THE EYES
OF THE LORD.

39:25.450 --> 39:27.234
PRAISE BE.
GOOD MORNING, SISTERS.

39:27.277 --> 39:30.542
WHAT MAY I SERVE THEE
WHILE YOU SERVE THE "ON HIGH"?

39:30.585 --> 39:33.022
WE'RE NOT HERE
FOR EARTHLY DELIGHTS.

39:33.066 --> 39:35.242
THE SISTERS ARE HERE
FOR SALVATION

39:35.285 --> 39:36.939
FROM THEIR BURDENED
BLADDERS.

39:36.983 --> 39:39.028
I'D HOPED THEY MIGHT
USE YOUR RESTROOM

39:39.072 --> 39:41.683
IN THIS, THEIR...TIME OF NEED.

39:41.727 --> 39:43.381
I LOVE THE GOD-LOVIN',

39:43.424 --> 39:46.645
BUT OUR RESTROOMS
ARE FOR CUSTOMERS ONLY.

39:46.688 --> 39:48.386
OH, GO ON, GIRLS.

39:48.429 --> 39:50.692
THE SISTERS
OF THE DIVINE MAGNATUM AND I

39:50.736 --> 39:53.303
ARE SPREADING THE GOOD WORD
IN THE COMMUNITY.

39:53.347 --> 39:54.783
WELL, I PRAY
THE GOOD WORD GETS SPREAD

39:54.827 --> 39:56.132
TO THE VERY EDGES
OF OUR COUNTRY

39:56.176 --> 39:58.004
AND SPILLS OVER
INTO OTHER COUNTRIES

39:58.047 --> 39:59.353
THAT MAY NOT BE LOOKING
FOR THE GOOD WORD --

39:59.397 --> 40:02.095
OR RECOGNIZE IT
WHEN THEY SEE IT.

40:02.138 --> 40:05.664
OR HEAR IT.
OR HEAR IT -- INDEED.

40:05.707 --> 40:08.406
YOU INSPIRE ME, BIG MAMA.

40:08.449 --> 40:09.929
THE PIE AND THE PEE
BREAK'S ON ME --

40:09.972 --> 40:12.932
IN THE NAME OF CHARITY,
OF COURSE.

40:12.975 --> 40:14.237
PEACE BE WITH YOU.

40:14.281 --> 40:16.892
AND ALSO WITH YOU,
MY CHILD.

40:16.936 --> 40:18.590
Narrator: WITH THE AID
OF MOTHER SUPERIOR,

40:18.633 --> 40:21.114
WHO'D BECOME
A SUPERIOR MOTHER FIGURE,

40:21.157 --> 40:23.682
OLIVE SNOOK HAD ARRANGED
FOR HER FATHER FIGURES

40:23.725 --> 40:26.598
TO CROSS THE BORDER,
AFTER ALL.

40:29.731 --> 40:32.473
WHILE THE PIE MAKER
AND A GIRL NAMED CHUCK

40:32.517 --> 40:34.475
REARRANGED THE STORAGE ROOM

40:34.519 --> 40:38.131
TO ACCOMMODATE THE INGREDIENTS
A SUPER PIE MAKER NEEDS.

40:38.174 --> 40:40.220
YOU'D THINK THAT STOCKING
DEAD FRUIT FOR BAKING WHILE

40:40.263 --> 40:42.309
WE WAITED FOR FRESH FRUIT
TO ROT WOULD BE DEPRESSING,

40:42.352 --> 40:44.267
BUT I FIND IT
SORT OF CATHARTIC.

40:44.311 --> 40:46.487
HMM. YEAH, THERE'S
A CERTAIN SATISFACTION

40:46.531 --> 40:48.184
IN PUTTING THINGS
BACK WHERE THEY BELONG.

40:48.228 --> 40:50.535
A RETURN TO NORMAL --
AT LEAST, "NORMAL" FOR US.

40:52.537 --> 40:56.192
I MISSED YOU ON
OUR BACHELOR-PARTY BORDER RUN.

40:56.236 --> 40:57.803
WELL, IT'S BETTER
THAT I DIDN'T GO.

40:57.846 --> 40:59.239
I WAS PEEVED
JUST THINKING ABOUT IT.

40:59.282 --> 41:00.980
PEEVED?

41:01.023 --> 41:03.199
ABOUT YOU AND OLIVE OUT
CELEBRATING YOUR RELATIONSHIP

41:03.243 --> 41:05.332
WHEN ALL WE DO
IS HIDE OURS.

41:05.375 --> 41:06.464
SO...

41:06.507 --> 41:08.248
YEAH, I WAS PEEVED.

41:08.291 --> 41:09.902
I WAS CELEBRATING
A FAKE RELATIONSHIP,

41:09.945 --> 41:12.034
AND THERE WERE
CIRCUMSTANCES AND DRAMA.

41:12.078 --> 41:13.122
I WAS EVADING THE LAW.

41:16.125 --> 41:17.910
ARE YOU JEALOUS OF OLIVE?

41:17.953 --> 41:19.781
OF COURSE I AM.

41:19.825 --> 41:22.349
I MEAN, SHE'S ALIVE AND
EVERYBODY KNOWS IT, FOR ONE.

41:22.392 --> 41:25.352
AND YOU GET TO SHARE
ROMANTIC ANECDOTES,

41:25.395 --> 41:28.311
AND THERE'S
NO PLOT HOLES.

41:28.355 --> 41:30.531
YOU DON'T HAVE TO WAIT
TILL WINTER TO HOLD HER HAND.

41:30.575 --> 41:32.620
THE ONLY HAND
I WANT TO HOLD IS YOURS,

41:32.664 --> 41:36.406
AND I...WILL WEAR WINTER
GLOVES YEAR-ROUND TO DO IT.

41:36.450 --> 41:38.539
SO DON'T BE JEALOUS.

41:38.583 --> 41:40.846
BESIDES, OLIVE IS
FINALLY OVER ME.

41:40.889 --> 41:44.458
EVEN WHEN I THOUGHT
I WAS DOING EVERYTHING
SHE WANTED ME TO DO...

41:44.502 --> 41:46.547
I STILL ENDED UP
HURTING HER.

41:46.591 --> 41:48.810
[ BOWL SLIDES ]

41:48.854 --> 41:52.466
Narrator:
THE GUILT THE PIE MAKER FELT
OVER THE HURT HE'D CAUSED

41:52.510 --> 41:54.816
WAS MIXED WITH A TINGE OF...

41:54.860 --> 41:56.601
SOMETHING.

41:56.644 --> 41:58.472
BUT HE DID NOT KNOW WHAT.

42:10.615 --> 42:13.356
THE PIE MAKER WATCHED RANDY
TAKE OLIVE'S HAND

42:13.400 --> 42:15.228
AND HOLD IT IN HIS.

42:15.271 --> 42:19.058
THEN, WITHOUT WARNING, HE KNEW
WHAT THAT SOMETHING WAS --

42:19.101 --> 42:22.844
THE TINGE HE HADN'T BEEN ABLE
TO IDENTIFY JUST MOMENTS AGO.

42:25.412 --> 42:26.631
JEALOUSY.
